research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0014.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current best family may need cleaner support suppression rather than another additive or multiplicative residual path. An adaptive-threshold TopK encoder that keeps the proven linear logits as the anchor but learns an input-dependent nonnegative per-latent suppression term could reduce false activations at K=128 and materially improve FVU without abandoning the strong baseline initialization.","summary":"The gated probe was a clear regression, so this round moves to a new architecture edit instead of more parameter-only tuning on weak recent families. The new `adaptive_threshold_topk` family starts exactly from plain TopK behavior and only learns to suppress linear logits, making it a focused quality-first prototype to test at the K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor under proxy.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"adaptive_threshold_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent architectural bet grounded in the strongest observed prior: keeping the linear TopK path intact. The main risk is that suppression-only flexibility may still be too weak to beat hybrid_topk, but it is safer and more targeted than the recent families that replaced or loosely mixed the baseline encoder.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_threshold_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/adaptive_threshold_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 14 adds a new adaptive_threshold_topk family that preserves the plain linear TopK encoder at initialization and learns only input-dependent nonnegative suppression of latent logits.","A quick local import/forward sanity check passed for adaptive_threshold_topk before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If adaptive_threshold_topk shows a strong proxy gain, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If adaptive_threshold_topk is flat or weak, the next round should bias toward a more expressive new architecture or a hybrid-family training-dynamics experiment rather than revisiting gated or jumprelu local sweeps."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The union_topk prototype likely failed because its nonlinear branch proposed candidates from the same centered input as the linear branch, so it mostly duplicated baseline support. Conditioning the nonlinear proposer on the linear branch residual, widening that branch, and letting it over-propose candidates before the final global top-k should increase support complementarity at K=128 and lower proxy FVU.","summary":"Stabilize the new union_topk family with a complementary-proposal encoder: the linear path still anchors selection, but the nonlinear branch now reads the linear residual and can surface extra candidates that the baseline top-k misses. This is a single quality-first proxy follow-up on the most recent new family, rather than another local sweep on hybrid_topk.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"union_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within one coherent family hypothesis and directly targets the main weakness of the round-16 prototype: redundant candidate proposals. The main risk is that proxy training may still be too short for the wider residual-conditioned branch to separate from the linear anchor, but this is a more informative family-specific follow-up than pivoting away after one near-baseline prototype.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"union_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/union_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 stabilizes union_topk by making the nonlinear proposal branch residual-conditioned on the linear partial reconstruction instead of reading the same centered input.","The union_topk stabilization also widens the nonlinear branch and lets it over-propose 2k candidates before the final global top-k, aiming to improve candidate diversity without changing decode semantics.","A local import/forward/backward sanity check passed for the edited union_topk implementation before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If residual-conditioned union_topk materially improves proxy FVU, promote this family toward mainline comparison and consider a full run.","If it remains near the recent 0.275 proxy plateau under normal runtime, pivot away from branch-union variants to a more radical encoder family rather than spending more rounds on local union_topk tuning."]}
