research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The stabilized factorized_topk crash was caused by an implementation bug in the widened hidden-path projection, not by the architecture itself. Fix the hidden-to-latent projection and rerun the same K=128 factorized_topk stabilization pass to recover a valid quality signal.","summary":"Round 5 produced a shape-mismatch crash inside factorized_topk after the widening edit, so the next move is a direct bug-fix rerun rather than abandoning the family. This keeps the hypothesis narrow: validate the intended wider gated factorized encoder before making any new architectural decision.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the correct response to the last round because the failure was a concrete code bug, not a training-quality outcome. The rerun is still only worth one more round; if the fixed version remains poor, this branch should be deprioritized.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 5 factorized_topk crashed due to a hidden-to-latent shape mismatch in the widened encoder path, so that result should not be treated as architectural evidence.","Round 6 fixes factorized_topk by adding an explicit hidden-to-latent projection and excluding the unused base encoder from optimization before re-running the same stabilization test."],"next_hypotheses":["If the fixed factorized_topk now yields a valid proxy improvement, keep incubating the family with quality-focused tuning.","If the fixed factorized_topk still performs poorly under normal runtime, stop spending rounds on current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder design."]}
