research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0083.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`adam` at the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor failed catastrophically, so the optimizer question is now cleanly resolved in favor of `signum`. The next single question should move to the loss axis rather than K or another architecture change: dropping `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` tests whether the current mainline is being mildly over-regularized and whether a cleaner reconstruction objective improves the mid/late training curve under the settled `signum` recipe.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, explicitly keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and changes exactly one primary variable on top of the settled `signum` anchor. The main risk is that the auxiliary term may still be helping latent usage even if its endpoint effect is small, but after the optimizer branch crashed the cleanest remaining mainline question is loss regularization rather than opening preprocess or moving K prematurely.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 83 closes the optimizer branch for `lowrank_two_stage_residual`: `adam` at the matched K128/EF12/LR=2.0e-3 anchor was a catastrophic failure, so `signum` remains the settled mainline optimizer.","This round opens the loss-axis check by testing `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` on the exact stable `signum` reference recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` regresses or destabilizes, restore `0.03125` and test exactly one preprocess variable next, such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` if still unexplored on this family.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that loss setting before moving to preprocess or K.","Do not move K until the K128 mainline has a settled optimizer and at least one resolved loss/preprocess verdict."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A thresholded sparse activation family may beat the current hybrid mainline by learning which latent logits should be suppressed before top-k selection rather than only reshaping logits with extra branches. Test jumprelu at K=128 with Adam as a fresh quality-first family probe.","summary":"The latest hybrid_topk edit was a normal-runtime regression, and several rounds have now been spent on local hybrid stabilization without another gain. This round shifts back to architecture exploration with an untried family whose learned thresholds could improve selectivity at the same K=128 anchor point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a deliberate reset to a genuinely different sparse activation mechanism after the hybrid local edits stalled. The risk is that JumpReLU may proxy poorly under the fixed-K implementation, but it is the cleanest untried family with a credible path to lower FVU.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The best current full frontier remains hybrid_topk with Adam at K=128, expansion_factor=8, FVU 0.16189537942409515.","Round 11 reopens architecture exploration after hybrid local edits stalled, using jumprelu as a new family with learned thresholding at fixed K=128."],"next_hypotheses":["If jumprelu shows a strong proxy signal, promote it to full before doing more hybrid tuning.","If jumprelu is flat or worse, keep hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 as mainline and then decide between a new encoder family or a training-dynamics experiment on the hybrid checkpoint."]}
