research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent hybrid and adaptive-threshold results suggest the main failure mode is not lack of an anchor but how nonlinear information is injected into support selection. A union_topk encoder that keeps the baseline linear top-k proposal intact while letting a nonlinear branch propose an alternate candidate set, with final support chosen from the union rather than from perturbed logits, could lower FVU by adding complementary features without destabilizing the proven linear path.","summary":"The orthogonality regularization follow-up regressed on both proxy FVU and throughput, so more local regularization sweeps are not justified. This round adds a new `union_topk` family under `sparsify/` and tests it first at the same K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor, probing whether branch-level candidate union is a better way to add encoder expressivity than the recent additive, gating, or suppression mechanisms.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"union_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent architecture bet that directly addresses the weakness exposed by recent edits: nonlinear branches have either interfered with or failed to improve baseline support. The risk is that merged candidate sets may still be too redundant to beat hybrid_topk, but the design preserves the strongest prior while giving the nonlinear branch a cleaner path to help.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"union_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/union_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 16 adds a new union_topk family that preserves the linear TopK proposal and lets a nonlinear branch contribute only through alternate candidate proposals before the final global top-k.","A quick local import and forward check passed for union_topk before returning control to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If union_topk shows a strong proxy gain, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If union_topk is flat or weak, the next round should either stabilize this branch-union family with a family-specific width change or pivot to a more radical new encoder design rather than returning to recent discarded regularization ideas."]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0118.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。当前 EF=2 已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，`signum + LR=3.0e-3` 是已复现的低成本主线锚点，而 `adam` 在同配方下直接爆炸，说明 optimizer 分支可暂时关闭。按主线顺序，下一步应进入 loss/preprocess 轴；本轮只改一个主变量 `AUXK_ALPHA`，将其从默认 `0.03125` 下调到 `0.015625`，回答唯一问题：在低 EF 可部署 regime 下，较弱的辅助稀疏正则是否能减少对主重构目标的干扰，从而改善 FVU，同时几乎不增加训练运行代价。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果较低 `AUXK_ALPHA` 改善终点或曲线形状，且 `tokens_per_sec`、总耗时、`final_total_tokens` 基本不变，则再做一次 clean baseline 复现确认。","如果较低 `AUXK_ALPHA` 无益或退化，则关闭该 loss 分支，保留默认 `0.03125` 并再考虑其他轻量 loss/preprocess 轴。","在 loss/preprocess 轴未得出清晰信号前，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式不变，仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","Optimizer 分支结论：`adam` 在 EF=2、LR=3.0e-3 下出现爆炸性退化，应回到 `signum + LR=3.0e-3` 主线锚点。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `AUXK_ALPHA`；这是 loss 轴上的轻量改动，不会改变 encoder 选择成本，也不应显著增加训练时长。重点继续检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 与 LR 轴已完成，optimizer 分支也因 `adam` 爆炸而得到负结论，因此现在应转向 loss/preprocess。选择 `AUXK_ALPHA` 而不是更重的 preprocess 变化，是因为它改动最小、归因最清晰、运行代价最低。","summary":"关闭 `adam` 分支，回到已复现的 `signum + LR=3.0e-3` 主线配方，仅将 `AUXK_ALPHA` 从 `0.03125` 下调到 `0.015625`，测试更弱辅助稀疏正则能否在低成本 EF=2 regime 下进一步改善 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
