research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0114.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都对应静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 112 与 Round 113 已在 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=2.4e-3 下复现同一可行 Pareto 点，说明成本预算内的 clean baseline 已确认；本轮只改一个主变量 `LR`，上探到 3.0e-3，回答唯一问题：在 EF=2 的低成本 regime 下，略高一步长能否在不牺牲稳定性和吞吐的前提下改善全程下降形状或终点 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 改善终点或明显加快早中期下降且运行代价未恶化，则将其作为新的 signum 主线学习率候选并考虑一次复现确认。","如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 出现震荡、退化或吞吐/总时长明显变差，则关闭向上 LR 分支，保留 `LR=2.4e-3` 作为 EF=2 主线锚点。","在 LR 轴结论明确前，不切换 optimizer、不改 K，也不改其他成本相关结构参数。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","EF=2 已在 Round 112 和 Round 113 下稳定落在选择成本预算内，当前 frontier 可行点为 cost≈1.25x、FVU≈0.05914。","本轮遵守单变量原则，只改 `lr`；重点同时观察曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`，避免为微小 FVU 改善付出过高运行代价。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认可行，clean baseline 已补齐，下一步应只做学习率局部化。选择向上探测而不是改 optimizer，是因为现有 EF=2 曲线已稳定但仍有继续下降迹象，最值得先测试的是更积极一步长是否能带来更好的收敛效率；同时没有引入第二个变量，归因清晰。","summary":"在已确认成本可行且可复现的 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` EF=2 主线上，仅将 `LR` 从 `2.4e-3` 上调到 `3.0e-3`，测试更高 signum 步长能否改善低成本 regime 的收敛曲线和终点 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0100.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 98 was the first signum learning-rate probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so the next single question is whether that higher step size is a real improvement or just run noise. Re-running the exact `LR=2.4e-3` recipe is still the cleanest test, and it should be judged by full-curve repeatability against the `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs rather than endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and rerun the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 retries the unresolved `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EF=12` after the previous confirmation attempt was policy-rejected rather than trained.","Judge this run by curve-shape repeatability versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 98 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
