research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 67 was rejected before execution, so the mainline still has only the archived clean baseline at `two_stage_residual` `K=128` `EF=12` `signum` `LR=2.0e-3`. The highest-value next single question remains the first within-family learning-rate probe: does a modest upward shift to `LR=2.4e-3` improve early and mid-course descent for `two_stage_residual` without destabilizing the curve, relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline.","summary":"Run a single learning-rate probe within the `two_stage_residual` mainline by keeping `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, and changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family and changes exactly one primary variable, which matches the Round 68 policy. Because the downward LR probe never actually ran, a modest upward LR test is the cleanest first recipe move from the confirmed baseline and directly checks whether the staged residual model is slightly under-driven at `2.0e-3`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 68 resumes mainline tuning after a policy-rejected Round 67, so the only valid executed baseline remains `two_stage_residual` at `LR=2.0e-3` with `signum`.","This round is the first executed LR probe for `two_stage_residual`; judge it by full curve shape against the archived baseline, especially whether higher LR improves descent without adding instability.","If `2.4e-3` is unstable or worse, the next LR move should go downward from the archived baseline rather than exploring optimizer yet."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` improves endpoint or overall curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is clearly worse or unstable, revert to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline and test `1.6e-3` next.","If `LR=2.4e-3` is mixed, use one more LR probe before considering an optimizer change."],"primary_variable":"learning_rate"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 47 answered the `K=32` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) did not collapse when support was cut in half again, and it now owns the `K=32` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the old control. The next single question is where that transfer finally breaks for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `24`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best point at that lower online cost, or does the advantage disappear below `K=32`?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=24` control (`0.272262`), then `gated` has established a meaningful mid-low-K foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=32` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, and `K=32`. The main risk is that `K=24` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for mapping the LUTurbo cost-quality boundary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=32`: it beat the previous `K=32` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 48 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=24`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@24` clearly beats the existing `K=24` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=16` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@24` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=32` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime.","summary":"Prototype a `group_topk` SAE family in `sparsify/` and run it in proxy at K=128 with the current strongest gated training settings to test whether local competition yields a better Pareto direction than plain top-k, gated, or routed support selection.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single architecture bet under severe stagnation and avoids more minor gated tuning. The main risk is that group-wise competition may be too restrictive at K=128, but it is a genuinely different sparse selection mechanism with a plausible diversity and throughput upside, and the code passed a local forward/backward sanity check.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"GROUP_TOPK_SIZE","value":"4"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added a new `group_topk` SAE family that selects one winner per local latent group before the global top-k stage, creating a different support-selection bias from top-k, gated, and routed.","Extended config validation with `group_topk_size` and registered `group_topk` in architecture dispatch so checkpoints and training can instantiate it through the existing execution layer.","Local sanity check passed for `group_topk`: forward/backward succeeded and returned the expected `(batch, k)` latent activations and indices."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` proxy FVU is competitive with gated and better than top-k/routed, keep the family alive and stabilize the group size as the next family-specific axis.","If `group_topk` quality is mediocre but throughput is materially better, treat it as a cost-quality tradeoff family and compare at smaller K rather than discarding it immediately.","If `group_topk` is clearly worse on both quality and runtime, retire local-competition support selection and move to a more expressive multi-branch or factorized encoder family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0215.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"192"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此兼容性为直接兼容。r214 已证明在 EF=1 下把 K 从 64 提到 128 能把 <0.5x 区域的 FVU 从 0.2583 压到 0.1968，说明当前低开销区的主瓶颈更像是查表预算不足，而不是 topk family 已经到头；因此本轮继续沿同一最短链路 family 提升 K 到 192，目标是在总成本仍预计约 0.43x、明显低于 0.5x 的条件下，进一步压低低开销区最佳 FVU，验证 topk@EF1 是否还能继续向可用前沿逼近。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K192 在 <0.5x 内继续明显改善 FVU 且吞吐下降可接受，则同 family 的低开销前沿可继续沿 K 轴补一个更细点。","如果 K192 的收益很小但训练时间或 tokens_per_sec 明显变差，则说明 EF=1 下继续堆 K 的边际收益开始耗尽，后续应转向新的低成本 family 而不是再加查表预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是当前唯一已在 <0.5x 区域稳定形成两个可行点的直接兼容 family，且导出路径最简单，适合作为低开销主线基准。","r214 已经给出明确正信号：在 EF=1 保持 encoder 成本不变时，增加 K 能显著改善 FVU，因此当前最有信息量的单变量仍是 K 轴。","评估时必须同步检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认新增查表预算是否值得。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮延续已验证有效的低开销 topk 主线，不再重复被 policy 卡住的 lowrank_factorized_residual param_only 路线。选择 K=192 而不是先补 K=96，是因为当前任务优先级是尽快把 <0.5x 区域的最佳 FVU 压低，而不是细化已明显被 K=128 支配的中间点；风险是更高 K 可能带来吞吐下降和更长总耗时。","summary":"继续使用直接兼容的 topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，把 K 提到 192，测试是否能在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的前提下，把低开销区最佳 FVU 从 0.1968 进一步压低。","touched_files":[]}
