research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 49 answered the `K=16` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=16` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally fails under extreme support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `8`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best ultra-low-cost point, or does the family advantage break once support becomes very tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=8` control (`0.380332`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the ultra-low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=16` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, `K=24`, and `K=16`. The main risk is that `K=8` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=16`: it beat the previous `K=16` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 50 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=8`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens sharply."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@8` clearly beats the existing `K=8` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=4` under the same recipe to locate the final break point.","If `gated@8` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=16` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` family may only be competitive at the largest support, so stepping `K` down from `128` to `96` while holding `EF=12`, `optimizer=signum`, and `lr=1.6e-3` tests one question only: does `gated` remain competitive on the adjacent frontier point, or is its apparent edge confined to `K=128`?","summary":"Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 begins the first K probe for gated after recipe tuning was exhausted: gated, K=96, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.","If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0035.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the gated family now improved at K=128 via AUXK_ALPHA=0.01, the next clean move is to test whether that stronger regime transfers to a smaller sparsity budget and improves the Pareto frontier rather than only the anchor point. A gated K=64 proxy run under the same stabilized settings can reveal whether the current best family can materially outperform the old JumpReLU K=64 point.","summary":"Run the stabilized gated configuration in proxy at K=64 with AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 to test whether the improved K=128 regime yields a stronger low-K Pareto point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"pareto","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps one coherent change on the current best working family and directly targets Pareto improvement at lower K instead of reopening weaker architecture branches immediately. The main risk is that gated may not transfer well to lower K, but that outcome is still informative because the existing K=64 frontier is substantially weaker than the current gated anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Reducing AUXK_ALPHA to 0.01 produced a new best full K=128 gated result, so this setting is the new gated stability anchor.","This round tests whether the improved gated regime transfers to lower K and can strengthen the Pareto frontier rather than only refining the anchor point.","Using the same architecture and optimizer isolates K as the only changed variable for a clean low-K comparison against the existing JumpReLU K=64 frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=64 proxy is clearly better than the current JumpReLU K=64 point, promote it to full and consider gated the new mainline family across multiple K values.","If gated K=64 is competitive but not clearly better, test whether a smaller expansion factor improves the low-K cost-quality tradeoff within the gated family.","If gated K=64 is poor, keep gated focused on K=128 quality work and revisit a different architecture family for lower-K exploration."],"primary_variable":"k"}
