research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0061.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Local gated sweeps have restored the stable baseline but are not closing the quality gap, and the most concrete unresolved blocker is still that `residual_topk` cannot be selected by the execution layer. The least-bad informative move is a narrow code round that registers and wires `residual_topk` into `SparseCoderConfig` validation and SAE class dispatch so the intended K=128 proxy prototype can finally produce a real quality signal.","summary":"Add `residual_topk` support under `sparsify/` and rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the existing signum regime.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the operator guidance to fix architecture-specific blockers before drawing quality conclusions, and it keeps the round focused on a single variable: making the blocked family runnable. The main risk is that registration is not the only incompatibility, but even that outcome is more informative than spending another round on incremental gated tuning.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The runtime policy still says quality is the primary objective, but recent gated param-only rounds are now yielding only marginal frontier movement rather than a step-change toward the aggressive FVU target.","`residual_topk` remains untested on quality because its recent failures were architecture-registration crashes in `sparsify/`, which should be treated as implementation blockers rather than evidence against the family.","This round should change only the SAE code needed to make `residual_topk` selectable and runnable by the existing launcher, keeping the prototype hyperparameters otherwise fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_topk` runs and shows competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal budget split next.","If `residual_topk` runs cleanly but is clearly worse than gated and not better than prior incubating families, archive it quickly and resume broader architecture exploration.","If `residual_topk` still fails after registration and dispatch are fixed, treat the remaining issue as a deeper implementation incompatibility and move to a different new family rather than continue local gated sweeps."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0105.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 104 promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to the EF=12 K128 frontier under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3` recipe, so the next single mainline question should be baseline stability rather than opening a new tuning branch immediately. Re-running the exact same `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` recipe will show whether Round 104 was a robust new anchor worth tuning from, and the decision should be based on the full curve shape, not only the final FVU.","summary":"Stay on the new `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and run a clean baseline confirmation with the exact reference recipe: `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with no other recipe changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required mainline sequence after a fresh architecture win: keep the new family, hold `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, optimizer, and LR fixed, and spend one round confirming that the improved result is repeatable before probing learning rate or optimizer. The tradeoff is delaying tuning by one round, but that is justified because recipe comparisons are only meaningful once the new baseline is shown to be stable.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 105 is a clean baseline confirmation for the newly promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`.","Judge this run by whole-curve repeatability versus Round 104, especially whether the early and mid training trajectory remains at least as strong as the promoted run rather than relying only on terminal FVU.","Do not open LR or optimizer tuning until this baseline has been confirmed or disproven cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If the baseline repeat matches or nearly matches Round 104 on curve shape and endpoint, open the within-family LR branch next, starting with one symmetric learning-rate probe.","If the repeat falls back materially or shows unstable curve shape, spend one more round resolving baseline robustness before tuning other recipe axes.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the new mainline baseline is localized."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history_archive/10_20260321_011318/logs/agent_action_0001.json:1:{"change_type":"edit_sae_code","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"A gated SAE with a separate support-selection encoder can reduce support interference versus plain TopK at K=128, improving FVU before spending effort on smaller-K or cost optimizations.","needs_sanity":true,"next_hypotheses":["If gated beats TopK on proxy FVU, expose and sweep gated_temperature to sharpen or soften support selection.","If gated shows quality promise but poor throughput, follow with a performance pass rather than discarding the family.","If gated underperforms badly at default settings, try a stabilization round on family-specific bias/temperature before abandoning the family."],"notes_to_memory":["Added a new 'gated' architecture family under sparsify/ with a separate gate encoder and default-compatible config fields.","Validated basic forward/backward and save/load for the new gated SAE locally before proposing the run.","Round stays focused on architecture exploration; K remains at the existing anchor and no lower-K claim is being made."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This is a clean prototype, but it increases encoder-side compute and parameter count. The launcher only exposes ARCHITECTURE today, so family-specific hyperparameters remain at defaults for this first incubation run.","summary":"Prototype the new gated SAE family and run a proxy comparison against the existing K=128 TopK anchor by switching ARCHITECTURE to gated.","touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0113.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都可静态导出为固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 112 已证明 EF=2 时该主线 family 进入选择成本预算内（约 1.25x h×n）并得到 FVU=0.05914，但这只是首个成本可行点。按当前主线顺序，下一轮应先补 clean baseline：完全复现 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=2.4e-3`，确认该低成本 Pareto 点是否可重复、曲线是否仍保持从 0.0966 -> 0.0655 -> 0.0591 的健康下降，而不是立即再动 LR 或其他配方轴。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 EF=2 clean baseline 复现出接近 0.059 的终点且曲线仍健康，再只改 `lr` 做单变量微调。","如果 clean baseline 明显回退或曲线形状不稳，则先把该点降级为不稳定候选，不急于开 optimizer 分支。","如果复现时仍显示 late-stage 继续改善且吞吐/总耗时稳定，再考虑是否需要更长训练而不是立刻改结构。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","Round 112 的 EF=2 可行点已满足成本预算，并且 `curve_still_improving=true`、`tokens_per_sec≈166553`、`final_total_tokens≈59.97M`，说明当前更需要确认可重复性而不是同时打开新配方轴。","本轮严格单变量原则下不再改变 EF/LR/optimizer/K；问题只是在低成本主线 recipe 上补一次 clean baseline。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"这符合当前策略顺序：先确认 EF 在预算内，再补 clean baseline。虽然 env_overrides 与 Round 112 相同，但这正是本轮要隔离的唯一问题，即该 EF=2 主线点是否稳定可复现。没有同时引入 LR、optimizer、K 或结构变化，归因最干净。","summary":"在当前成本可行主线 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 上补一次 clean baseline，完整复现 `EF=2, K=128, signum, LR=2.4e-3`，先确认这个 LUTurbo 可部署 Pareto 点的稳定性与曲线形状，再决定是否进入 LR 微调。","touched_files":[]}
