research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` was the first recent matched probe to land relatively close to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, so the next most informative architecture-only question is whether that coarse static codebook branch remains viable when the sparse residual selector is made cheaper. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library decomposition as the soft-codebook probe, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection. If it stays reasonably close under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this family may offer a better quality-versus-online-selection-cost tradeoff than the mainline; if it falls back to the weaker grouped-single-stage pattern, then the earlier soft-codebook result should be treated as requiring full global selection to matter.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. It is a stronger LUTurbo-aligned probe than opening a heavier two-stage soft-codebook branch, because grouped local competition directly targets lower online selection cost while retaining the promising coarse static codebook decomposition seen in Round 92. The risk is that the grouped selector may erase most of the quality gain that made `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` interesting, in which case this family should be deprioritized quickly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for combining a coarse static codebook branch with cheaper group-local sparse selection; the key question is whether the Round 92 soft-codebook signal survives a more deployment-friendly selector.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not turn this into a multi-round soft-codebook branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than both `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` and the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard grouped soft-codebook variants and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` remains surprisingly close to the mainline, record it as a potentially lower-selection-cost branch but still return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0154.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r153 已用 clean baseline 重新确认主线参考配方在当前运行环境下能稳定回到 FVU≈0.058106 且总耗时降回 294s，说明近期慢速样本更像吞吐波动而非 family 退化；因此本轮只回答一个问题：在主线 family、K、EF、optimizer 与导出形式不变的前提下，把 LR 从 3.0e-3 上调到此前两次出现更低终点的 3.3e-3，能否在正常吞吐区间内稳定复现更好的中后段收敛与更低 FVU，而不是仅仅依赖异常慢速运行。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 3.3e-3 在接近 r153 的 tokens_per_sec/总耗时下再次稳定优于 3.0e-3，则把 3.3e-3 升格为该 family 的 signum 主线 LR。","若 3.3e-3 回落到接近 3.0e-3，或只有在明显更慢时才略优，则关闭 LR 上调分支，保留 3.0e-3 作为更稳的主线锚点。","若 3.3e-3 终点更好但曲线出现更早震荡或平台，则不再继续上探 LR，后续只在已确认较优的 LR 上考虑 optimizer 或更贴近系统成本的单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 继续满足选择成本预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 轴混杂。","r153 clean baseline 恢复到 294s，说明近期 391s/453s 更可能是吞吐异常而非训练更长。","评估本轮时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，判断 3.3e-3 的收益是否独立于运行时慢速样本。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。按照推荐顺序，EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 已补齐，现在进入学习率轴是最小且可归因的下一步。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 固定的前提下，仅把 LR 从 3.0e-3 调到 3.3e-3，验证此前的小幅 FVU 改善能否在正常运行代价下稳定复现。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0024.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 23 showed that increasing `AUXK_ALPHA` above the `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.6e-3` reference did not improve the anchor recipe, which suggests the mainline is likely saturated on auxiliary-loss magnitude itself. This round changes only `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD`, lowering it from the effectively inactive `10000000` to `100000`, to test whether earlier dead-feature rescue improves late-stage reconstruction or curve shape without changing the core topk recipe.","summary":"Run a single loss-schedule test on the exact topk mainline reference recipe: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` fixed, and reduce `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD` to `100000` to see whether activating auxiliary rescue earlier helps the K128 baseline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes only one non-core variable on the exact reference backbone, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the evidence that both weaker and stronger `AUXK_ALPHA` failed to beat the baseline. The main risk is that the threshold change may have little effect over this training horizon, but it is the cleanest remaining single-variable way to probe whether the auxiliary mechanism is mis-timed rather than mis-scaled.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"100000"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 14 (`AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625`) and Round 23 (`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625`) both failed to improve the K128 anchor, so the mainline loss axis now looks saturated on magnitude.","The next clean question is whether the auxiliary dead-feature mechanism is mistimed rather than misweighted; the current threshold `10000000` is effectively inactive over this run length.","Judge this run by full curve shape as well as final FVU: if earlier rescue smooths late descent or lowers FVU, the issue was activation timing; if not, the current topk/signum/K128 recipe is likely saturated on the aux-loss path."],"next_hypotheses":["If lowering `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD` improves the K128 reference, continue refining that schedule on the same backbone before moving to other recipe axes.","If earlier dead-feature rescue does not help, treat the current loss path as saturated and move to a different single recipe variable.","If lowering the threshold hurts stability or reconstruction, keep the effectively inactive dead-feature schedule as the better mainline choice."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0165.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static soft-codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is 扩展兼容: LUTurbo can export it as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + one residual sparse lookup, all over fixed vector libraries. The single question for this probe is whether removing the second residual refinement stage keeps enough reconstruction quality to justify the lower encoder selection cost and likely lower runtime in the low-EF regime.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If FVU regresses materially versus the mainline while runtime savings are small, return to lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual next round and stop probing nearby parents.","If runtime improves meaningfully at only modest FVU loss, keep lowrank_soft_codebook_residual as a cost-efficient compatible branch on the Pareto frontier, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export path is static trunk library + static codebook library + static residual dictionary; no dynamic decoder weights.","This is a matched architecture probe that changes only ARCHITECTURE and stays safely within the known EF=2 selection-cost budget table.","Probe intent is architectural value judgment only: test whether the second sparse stage in the current mainline is worth its extra encoder cost/runtime under LUTurbo constraints."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This probe is conservative because the family is already known and compatible, so upside is mostly in runtime-cost tradeoff rather than discovering a new best FVU. That makes it appropriate after the previous matched probe was policy-rejected: it isolates a single structural difference and should yield a clean comparable signal.","summary":"Run a single matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. The probe tests whether the simpler one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continuing as a lower-cost LUTurbo-compatible branch relative to the current two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0039.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`group_topk` still has no valid quality signal because its first actual proxy run timed out at the first step, which is stronger evidence of an implementation bottleneck than of a bad architecture. The next coherent move is a performance-focused code pass that makes the `group_topk` encoder path more execution-friendly so the family can receive one clean proxy measurement at K=128 under the strongest current regime.","summary":"Optimize the `group_topk` encoder implementation in `sparsify/` to eliminate the first-step timeout, then rerun the same K=128 proxy comparison under the current gated anchor settings.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the narrowest informative follow-up because round 38 failed before producing architectural evidence, and another family switch would leave the existing prototype unresolved. The main risk is spending a round on a bottleneck that still leaves `group_topk` uncompetitive, but that is preferable to misclassifying a timeout as a negative quality result.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/fused_encoder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 produced a `first_step_timeout` for `group_topk`, so the family still lacks a real proxy quality measurement.","Treat the timeout as an implementation issue first, not as evidence that local grouped competition is architecturally bad.","This round keeps the same `group_topk` K=128 comparison target and changes only the code path needed to obtain a valid run."],"next_hypotheses":["If the optimized `group_topk` path runs normally and is competitive with gated at K=128, keep the family alive and begin architectural refinement within the grouped-selection idea.","If the optimized run completes but remains clearly worse on FVU, retire hard local grouping and move to a more expressive encoder family.","If `group_topk` still times out after the code fix, conclude that this implementation path is not viable in the current stack and shift architecture exploration elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
