research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:2103:    "NOTE: The EF=1 `topk` K ladder has shown consistent FVU improvement from K=96 to K=128 to K=192 without any compatibility risk; an untested midpoint K=160 is the cleanest next `<0.5x` frontier probe.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:2111:      "change_type": "param_only",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0224.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM","value":"96"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r β_r u_r + Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算 trunk 系数 β_r 与 residual 稀疏系数 α_i，再执行 trunk 查表 + residual 查表 + 加权求和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。r223 已确认 `topk@EF1,K248` 的 recipe 轴继续向上推 LR 只带来更差 FVU 和明显更差吞吐，说明当前 <0.5x 最强 topk 锚点已基本饱和；同时 r221 说明直接压 `TRUNK_RANK` 会破坏 lowrank_factorized_residual 的 trunk 表达。基于 r210 这个高质量参考点，本轮严格只改一个 env 参数 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`，保留 `K=64, EF=1, signum, LR=3e-3` 与完整 trunk 分支不变，用更短的 factorized scorer 链路替代默认较宽隐藏层，测试是否能把该 family 的 total_cost 从 0.69x 压到约 0.48x，同时尽量保留显著优于同成本 topk 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 在约 0.48x 成本下仍明显优于 `topk@0.48x` 的 FVU=0.1483，且训练吞吐没有像 r221 那样恶化，则下一轮相对本轮继续单变量下探到 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=64`，寻找更低成本拐点。","如果 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 的 FVU 明显退化到接近或差于同成本 topk，则说明该 family 的优势主要来自更宽 scorer 而非 trunk 本身；下一轮应关闭这条 scorer 压缩线，转向新的低成本 family。","如果该配置质量接近 r210 但系统代价明显更差，则保留其为解释性对照，不继续把该 family 作为 <0.5x 主战场。"],"notes_to_memory":["r223 给出明确负面信号：`topk@EF1,K248` 的向上 LR 分支已不值得继续，后续应把注意力从 topk recipe 清洗转回新低成本结构。","本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 的 combined_ratio 约为 0.48x，已进入当前重点搜索区间，而不需要再次牺牲 trunk。","与压 `TRUNK_RANK` 不同，压 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM` 只缩短 factorized scorer 链路，保留 trunk 静态库的容量，更符合当前“降低选择成本但不破坏导出结构”的目标。"],"reference_round":210,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效参考轮 r210 只改 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`，family、K、EF、optimizer、LR 及其他结构参数全部不变。选择 96 而不是 128，是因为 128 只会把总成本压到约 0.50x 边界，仍不够明确进入当前主目标区；选择 96 而不是更激进的 64，则是为了先做最小但有效的 scorer 压缩，尽量保留 r210 已证明存在的质量优势。","summary":"相对 r210 的 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1` 做一次严格 param_only 低成本压缩，仅设置 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`，验证保留完整 trunk 时，缩短 factorized scorer 链路能否把该 family 推入 `<0.5x` Pareto 主前沿。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0228.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"240"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"frontier_mapping","hypothesis":"候选 family: jumprelu。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；JumpReLU 只改变单样本在线侧的阈值化支持形成与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 r227 只改一个 env 参数 `K=240`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH=0.05`、`JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD=0.02`、`signum`、`LR=0.003` 不变，测试在已经于 0.49x 成本点优于 topk 的前提下，轻微缩短查表链路后是否仍能保持对同成本邻近 topk 点的质量优势，从而补出 `<0.5x` 区域更低 deployment 成本一侧的 Pareto 前沿。该改动只降低部署查表成本，不增加 encoder 成本，total_cost 预计将从约 0.49x 小幅降到约 0.48x，仍稳居当前主战区且满足 LUTurbo 总成本硬约束。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `jumprelu@K240` 仍明显优于当前同区间 `topk@K240` 的 FVU=0.14833，且训练总时长不恶化，则继续相对本轮单变量下探到 `K=224`，补齐更低部署成本侧的 jumprelu 前沿形状。","如果 `K=240` 的 FVU 与 r227 基本持平或只小幅变差，但 wall-clock 更短，则可将 jumprelu 视为当前 `<0.5x` 区域同时更强且更便宜的默认直兼容主线，并减少对同一点 recipe 的继续清洗。","如果 `K=240` 的 FVU 退化过快，说明当前 jumprelu 改善主要依赖极高 K 支持预算；则关闭该 family 的 K 下探线，转向新的低成本 family 或回到更高质量锚点解释。"],"notes_to_memory":["r225-r227 已连续证明 jumprelu 在同成本高 K 单库 regime 下优于 topk，其中 r227 的 FVU=0.14564 已低于当前 topk@K248 的 0.14621。","当前最高信息量问题已不再是继续在 `K=248` 单点上做 recipe 微调，而是判断这条直接兼容单库路线能否沿 K 轴向更低部署成本扩展，真正补出 `<0.5x` Pareto 前沿。","评估本轮必须同时看 FVU、tokens_per_sec、duration_sec、final_total_tokens；如果只是极小质量变化但运行明显更慢，则不能视为正面信号。"],"reference_round":227,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r227 只改 `K`，不联动 architecture、EF、LR、bandwidth、init_threshold 或其他 recipe。选择沿 jumprelu 的 K 轴补前沿，而不是继续上探阈值，是因为 r227 已经把同成本质量点做到了优于 topk；当前更有价值的是确认它是否能在更低 deployment 成本邻域也保持优势，从而真正扩展 `<0.5x` frontier，而不是继续在同一点做密集局部优化。主要风险是质量对高 K 依赖过强，但这正是本轮要隔离回答的单一问题。","summary":"相对 r227 的 `jumprelu@EF1,K248,JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH=0.05,JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD=0.02` 做一次严格 param_only frontier probe，仅将 `K` 下调到 `240`。目标是在略降总成本的同时，验证 jumprelu 能否继续压过当前 `topk@0.48x` 邻近点，从而补出 `<0.5x` 区域更低部署成本侧的 Pareto 前沿。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0101.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 98 and 100 now make `LR=2.4e-3` the reproducible best signum setting for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, so the next single mainline question is optimizer choice. Testing `OPTIMIZER=adam` on that settled recipe will show whether this family's remaining limitation is optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the decision should be based on the whole curve shape versus the archived signum anchor, not just the endpoint.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after localizing the signum LR branch: same family, same `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is that `adam` may want a different LR than `signum`, but this first optimizer comparison is still the correct isolated question before spending any round on an optimizer-local LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 101 opens the optimizer branch for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 mainline after `signum` with `LR=2.4e-3` reproduced the best curve/endpoint.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the settled signum anchor at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.4e-3`, especially whether `adam` is smoother or more competitive through mid and late training rather than only comparing final FVU.","If `adam` is promising, it earns exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next; if it is clearly worse or unstable, keep `signum` and move on to loss or preprocess before touching `K`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the settled signum anchor, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable at `LR=2.4e-3`, close the optimizer branch in favor of `signum` and move to one loss-side or preprocess question next.","Do not change `K` until the optimizer question has been resolved cleanly on this family."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0038.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The last round showed the gated low-K capacity cut was a real quality regression, and the search has now gone several rounds without advancing an incubating alternative family. The least-bad informative move is to get a real proxy read on the already-implemented `group_topk` family at K=128 under the strongest current training regime, removing the unsupported `GROUP_TOPK_SIZE` override that caused the earlier policy crashes. This will finally test whether local winner-take-all competition can beat other non-gated support selectors on anchor-quality rather than being discarded for an execution-layer mismatch.","summary":"Run the first real proxy comparison for `group_topk` at K=128 using the current strongest gated training regime, but without the unsupported `GROUP_TOPK_SIZE` env override that caused the earlier crashes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This advances an incubating family instead of spending another round on weak local gated tuning, and it specifically resolves prior `group_topk` crashes as execution-layer issues rather than architectural evidence. The main risk is that hard local competition may still be too restrictive to challenge gated on FVU, but one clean proxy run is necessary before deciding whether to retire or stabilize this family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 32-33 did not provide architectural evidence on `group_topk`; they were rejected because `GROUP_TOPK_SIZE` is not an allowed execution-layer override.","This round retries `group_topk` with only allowed overrides so the family gets its first actual proxy measurement under the current strongest K=128 training regime.","Using the gated anchor settings at K=128 isolates architecture as the primary changed variable and gives a clean read on whether local competition is a viable quality direction."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` is competitive with gated at K=128, keep the family alive and follow with a code-round that softens or enriches the grouped selection mechanism inside `sparsify/`, since group-size sweeps are not exposed by the execution layer.","If `group_topk` is clearly worse on quality under a normal run, retire hard local grouping and move to a more expressive multi-branch or factorized encoder family instead of more support-ranking variants.","If `group_topk` is mediocre on FVU but materially better on runtime or memory, evaluate it as a cost-quality tradeoff family before discarding it."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 41 made the optimizer question clear: `gated+adam` is not merely slightly worse under the updated anchor, it shows the same pathological curve shape as before, with a strong mid-training blow-up and a much worse endpoint than `signum`. With the optimizer branch now effectively closed, the next single question in the prescribed order is loss: under the strengthened `gated` mainline recipe at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3`, is the default auxiliary loss actually helping, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the same family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one non-core variable after the optimizer branch was cleanly falsified twice. I am not spending another round on Adam LR because the updated `adam` trial was not borderline or merely mistuned; it repeated the same qualitative failure pattern and got worse at the stronger anchor. The main risk is that aux removal may have only a small effect, but it is now the next most policy-clean question before preprocess or K movement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 41 strongly rejected `adam` for `gated` again: compared with the `signum` anchor it showed the same mid-curve blow-up pattern as the earlier `adam` trial and finished far worse, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed.","Round 42 returns to the updated `gated+signum` anchor at `LR=2.0e-3` and isolates the loss axis by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` to test whether the default auxiliary term is still helping under the stronger mainline recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the curve or final FVU, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation on the same anchor.","If removing aux is worse or neutral, restore the default loss setting and move to the preprocess axis before any further K exploration."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
