research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.","summary":"Round 36 changed the picture: `gated@96` is not just viable, it improved the frontier over the existing `topk@96` control, so the family has earned one more K-mapping round. Keep the anchored recipe fixed and step only `K` from `96` to `64`. This directly answers whether the `gated` advantage generalizes to the next adjacent frontier point. Read the full curve, not just the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes below the `topk@64` control (`0.1992608`), `gated` is a real high-K mainline candidate; if it drops back behind `topk`, then the family likely helps only in the upper-K regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current family, keeps EF fixed at 12, and changes exactly one main variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed ordering because recipe tuning was already exhausted before K moves began, and `K=64` is the highest-value next probe after the successful `K=96` result.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 established that gated generalizes beyond K=128 by beating the matched topk control at K=96.","Round 37 should probe the next adjacent K point, gated@64 with the same signum/LR anchor, to test whether the advantage persists deeper into the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@64` also beats `topk@64`, continue one more downward K probe because gated is shaping up as the stronger mainline family across multiple frontier points.","If `gated@64` falls back behind `topk@64`, treat gated as a high-K specialist and preserve it mainly for K>=96."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 55 made the optimizer question clear on the strengthened recipe: `gated+adam` with `USE_HADAMARD=1` was not borderline or merely slower, it regressed badly to `0.285949`, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed and `signum` remains the correct mainline optimizer. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore loss under the current strengthened anchor: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, is the default auxiliary loss still helping, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory now that preprocessing has changed conditioning?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current signum anchor. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if dropping the auxiliary term yields a smoother or lower start/mid/late trajectory than the current `0.142923` anchor, then the strengthened recipe no longer wants the default aux loss; if it is neutral or worse again, restore the default loss and treat the mainline recipe as fully clarified before any further movement.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `loss`. It also follows the requested sequence cleanly after the Hadamard-enabled optimizer test failed decisively: there is no justification for an Adam LR callback, so the next informative mainline question is whether the strengthened signum recipe still benefits from the default auxiliary loss.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 55 strongly rejected `adam` on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor: the run finished at `0.285949`, far worse than the `signum` anchor, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed for the strengthened recipe as well.","Round 56 should isolate the loss question on the current strengthened `gated` anchor by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` at fixed `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, evaluating full curve shape rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` curve or endpoint, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation on the same anchor.","If removing aux is neutral or worse again, restore the default loss and treat the strengthened `gated` mainline recipe as settled before considering any further axis."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 45 showed that the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) transfers from `K=128` down to `K=96`, improving the prior `gated@96` result while keeping a smooth, still-improving curve. The next single question is whether that gain carries one more step down the cost ladder: if we hold the improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `64`, can `gated` produce a clearly better lower-cost point than the old `K=64` result, or does the Hadamard benefit fade before this support level?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 43-45 established a stronger `gated` mainline recipe: `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, with reproducible improvement at `K=128` and successful transfer to `K=96`.","Round 46 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether that improved recipe also lowers `gated@64` enough to strengthen the lower-cost part of the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@64` clearly beats the old `K=64` result with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=32` under the same recipe to locate where the transfer breaks.","If `K=64` regresses toward the old control or shows weaker curve quality, stop the downward sweep and treat the improved recipe mainly as a `K=96/128` high-quality lane."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0052.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Plain gated/local parameter sweeps have revalidated the low-K frontier but are not closing the quality gap, and the session has gone eight rounds without advancing a new family. A minimal `factorized_topk` prototype that inserts a low-rank ReLU mixing stage before hard top-k selection could improve support quality at K=128 while staying cheaper than a full dense two-branch encoder, so the next round should finally give this family a real proxy measurement under the current strongest signum regime.","summary":"Run a K=128 proxy prototype for the newly wired `factorized_topk` architecture under the current best signum settings to test whether low-rank encoder mixing can beat plain top-k/gated quality.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the smallest architecture-exploration step that respects the current stability rules: the code change is confined to `sparsify/`, passes a forward/backward sanity check, and resolves the concrete registration blocker that prevented any real signal from this family. The main risk is throughput or weak quality from the unfused two-layer encoder, but that would still be informative and separable from the earlier launcher/config failure.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Registered `factorized_topk` in `SparseCoderConfig` validation and SAE class dispatch so the execution layer can actually launch the family.","Implemented a minimal `factorized_topk` prototype with a low-rank ReLU mixing stage before latent scoring; hidden width is derived from existing config (`max(d_in/2, 4*K)`) so no launcher changes are required.","Local forward/backward sanity passed for `factorized_topk` at K=128, so the prior failure mode was a code-integration blocker rather than an architecture-quality result."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` completes and shows promising proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal width/throughput tradeoff next.","If it runs but is clearly worse than gated and plain top-k, archive this shallow factorized path and move to a different encoder-expressivity family.","If quality is plausible but runtime is poor, follow with an `edit_perf_code` round focused on the factorized encoder path rather than discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0106.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 104 and 105 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this two-stage soft-codebook recipe is slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required sequence after confirming the new baseline: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but this is the cleanest first LR-localization question before considering an upward probe or opening the optimizer branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 106 is the first LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the archived `LR=2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the lower step size improves late descent or only slows the whole curve.","If `LR=1.6e-3` regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves endpoint or late-curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new mainline LR for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly slower or worse, test only the symmetric upward probe at `LR=2.4e-3` next before opening the optimizer branch.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the signum LR bracket is localized."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
