research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0054.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The first real `factorized_topk` proxy run produced a clean signal instead of a crash, so the family has earned one stabilization pass before retirement. The most informative single-variable follow-up is to increase dictionary width at fixed K=128 and fixed optimization settings, testing whether the low-rank pre-mixing path was quality-limited by latent capacity rather than by the factorized design itself.","summary":"Run a `factorized_topk` proxy stabilization pass with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` at K=128 under the same signum baseline to test whether more latent capacity materially improves its proxy FVU.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one coherent variable, preserves the now-working family, and answers the next obvious question after a clean but weak prototype result: was the architecture bottlenecked by capacity. The main risk is spending one more round on a family that is still well behind gated, but a width check is the cheapest way to determine whether `factorized_topk` has headroom or should be archived.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` now has one valid proxy measurement: FVU 0.3275916539132595 at K=128, which is weak versus gated but good enough to justify one stabilization check instead of immediate retirement.","The next discriminating question is whether the family is fundamentally weak or merely under-capacity at the current width.","This round keeps architecture, K, optimizer, LR, and AUXK fixed and changes only expansion factor to probe latent-capacity sensitivity inside the incubating family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` improves materially with higher expansion, keep the family alive and continue stabilizing its width/throughput tradeoff.","If higher expansion barely helps, archive `factorized_topk` and redirect architecture exploration to a different family.","If quality improves but runtime regresses sharply, follow with a targeted performance-focused round instead of discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0007.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"回到直接兼容 family `topk`，最终重构公式为 `x_hat = Σ_{i in S(x)} α_i(x) b_i`。导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时，`{b_i}` 仍是单个静态向量库；在线继续执行 top-k 选择、系数计算、查表 `W b_i`、加权求和，并可保留选择性补偿接口。本轮相对 r1 仅调整训练配方中的 `LR`，在保持 `ARCHITECTURE=topk, K=64, EXPANSION_FACTOR=1` 不变的同一成本与结构槽位下，检查当前主线是否只是学习率未对齐导致曲线早早停滞。","summary":"兼容性判断：`topk` 为直接兼容。当前已经连续 3 轮未带来实质改进，且本轮策略明确要求先把同一 family 的 recipe 与训练曲线看清；因此不再继续切换 family，而是回到当前最佳主线点 `topk@K=64,EF=1` 做一次最小 recipe probe。将 `LR` 从 `8e-4` 下调到 `6e-4` 不改变 total_cost（仍约 `0.31x`），但能回答现有 signum 训练是否因步长偏大而在当前 hookpoint 上损失了后段收敛质量。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"遵守单变量原则，基于 `reference_round=1` 仅修改 `LR`。这轮问题单一且归因清晰：在最优低成本主线点上，收敛是否受学习率限制。如果 `LR=6e-4` 仍不能带来曲线改善，则可以更有根据地认定当前 `topk` 主线 recipe 已基本摸清，下一步应转向新的结构方向或高优先级未验证方案。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"LR","value":"6e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`topk@K=64,EF=1` 仍是当前 `<0.5x` 区域的主线最佳点，Round 7 先做同 family 的最小 recipe 校准。","`LR` 调整不改变 LUTurbo 成本槽位，可直接用于判断当前 signum 曲线是否存在步长过大导致的收敛停滞。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=6e-4` 改善了后段 FVU，可继续在 `topk@K=64` 附近做小幅 recipe 精修。","如果 `LR=6e-4` 仍无明显改善，则应停止继续打磨当前 `topk` recipe，转向新的兼容结构族或准备轻量 expert 子库方向。"],"reference_round":1}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0117.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都可静态导出为固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。当前主线在 EF=2 下已稳定满足 encoder 选择成本硬约束，且 signum 的 LR 轴已基本收敛：`LR=3.0e-3` 两轮复现优于 `2.4e-3`，而 `3.6e-3` 回退到 `FVU=0.058151...`，说明继续上探学习率的价值已下降。本轮只改一个主变量 `optimizer`，把 `OPTIMIZER` 从 `signum` 切到 `adam`，其余保持 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, LR=3.0e-3` 不变，回答唯一问题：在同样成本与部署形态下，adam 是否能带来更好的低成本 Pareto 点或更优曲线形状。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `adam` 在 `LR=3.0e-3` 下曲线健康且终点接近或优于 `signum`，则给 `adam` 一次单变量 LR 回调机会。","如果 `adam` 明显更差、发散或运行代价明显恶化，则关闭 optimizer 分支，保留 `signum + LR=3.0e-3` 为 EF=2 主线锚点。","在 optimizer 问题解决前，不改 K，也不改 TRUNK_RANK / NUM_CODES / STAGE1_RATIO / FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","LR 轴结论：`LR=3.0e-3` 是当前更稳的 signum 主线候选；`LR=3.6e-3` 未带来改进，因此应停止继续上探。","本轮严格单变量，只改 `optimizer`；评估时继续同时检查曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`，避免用更高训练代价换取不显著收益。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 已补齐，LR 轴也已通过 `3.0e-3` 与 `3.6e-3` 的结果基本收束，下一步应进入 optimizer 分支。保持 LR、EF、K 不变，只改 `optimizer`，归因清晰，并且遵守单变量原则。","summary":"停止继续上探 signum 学习率，转而在同一低成本主线配方上仅将 `OPTIMIZER` 从 `signum` 切到 `adam`，测试是否能在 EF=2 的可部署 regime 下得到更好的曲线或终点 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0061.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_grouped_residual` may need a slightly less aggressive low-K budget than `K=32` for its grouped residual routing to show useful quality at the required small-capacity setting, so the next informative move is a same-family probe at `K=40`, `EF=8` before changing EF or abandoning the grouped residual direction.","summary":"Keep the new `lowrank_grouped_residual` family fixed and run a proxy comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with the same optimizer/LR recipe. This preserves the small-EF constraint, continues lower-K mapping, and tests whether group-local competition plus a low-rank trunk becomes viable with a modestly looser sparse budget.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within one variable by changing only `K` on the newly introduced family. Risk is that the family may still be fundamentally weak, but `K=40` is the least-cost next point to determine whether the grouped residual mechanism has a usable low-K regime before pivoting again.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 61 keeps the new `lowrank_grouped_residual` family fixed and changes only `K` from the initial low-K anchor to map whether grouped residual routing needs a slightly larger sparse budget at `EF=8`.","This is a same-EF, lower-K-focused follow-up on a fresh architecture family rather than another cross-EF comparison or minor optimizer sweep.","If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is still clearly weak, treat grouped residual routing as likely non-competitive in the current small-EF band and pivot to another fundamentally different low-K mechanism."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` shows competitive proxy quality or better runtime regularity, continue the family with a nearby K comparison such as `K=32` versus `K=48` before touching EF.","If `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` remains weak, pivot to another fundamentally different architecture at the same `K=32` or `K=40`, `EF=8` target rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0113.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After fourteen non-improving rounds, the next useful move is still a fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff by letting multiple low-rank residual branches specialize instead of forcing one shared residual pathway.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the recent K=24 probes across gated, JumpReLU, and bucketed low-rank variants all failed to improve the current frontier. The next clean architecture comparison should stay on the valuable `K=24` anchor but switch to `lowrank_multi_branch_residual`, which offers a more structurally distinct conditional-composition mechanism than the selector variants tried in rounds 110 to 112 while keeping the stable EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe fixed. This isolates architecture alone and tests whether branch specialization helps where recent selector changes did not.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than making another minor tweak, keeps K within the allowed operator set, and targets a meaningful smaller-K frontier slot. The main risk is that prior older-budget evidence for this family was weak, but it remains a more distinct and defensible next probe than revisiting recently failing selector-style branches.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `bucketed_lowrank_residual` also lost at `K=24`, recent conditional-routing and selector-focused low-rank branches remain uncompetitive against the current mid-K frontier.","Round 113 should test `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as a more structurally different branch-specialization mechanism.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture rather than recipe drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the branch-specialization benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to recent selector or routing variants.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
