research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0008.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At fixed K=128, a Hadamard-rotated factorized_topk SAE with a narrow nonlinear hidden mixing stage will beat the current rotated linear top-k proxy anchor on FVU by giving the encoder more expressive support selection than a single linear projection, without changing the fixed-K decode path.","summary":"Add a new factorized_topk prototype under sparsify/ and run it as a proxy at K=128 with Hadamard and the baseline signum optimizer. This is a quality-first architecture exploration step after the residual_topk stabilization regression, so the next move is a different higher-expressivity encoder family rather than another weak local sweep.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows research/program.md: one coherent hypothesis, proxy by default, and architecture exploration after a normal-health residual_topk follow-up regressed. The implementation stays entirely under sparsify/, preserves the fixed execution layer, and passed a local instantiation plus forward/backward sanity check. The main risk is that the added nonlinearity may make optimization harder under signum, so a weak first proxy would argue for either optimizer-specific stabilization or abandoning this family quickly.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/__init__.py","sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Read research/program.md before deciding; after the residual_topk stabilization pass regressed under normal runtime, the right next move is a new quality-first architecture family rather than more narrow local tuning.","No operator_hints were present in the structured context for this round.","Added a factorized_topk prototype that inserts a narrow nonlinear hidden projection before latent scoring, keeping the standard decoder and fixed-K top-k interface intact.","Local sanity check passed for factorized_topk: Python instantiation plus forward/backward succeeded on a toy tensor, so the family is compatible with the existing SparseCoder training path."],"next_hypotheses":["If factorized_topk shows promising proxy FVU, keep the family alive with a stabilization pass over optimizer or orthogonality regularization before considering any smaller-K search.","If factorized_topk improves quality but shows a runtime regression, follow with an edit_perf_code pass on the extra hidden projection path instead of discarding the family.","If factorized_topk is clearly weak on proxy FVU, move on to a different higher-expressivity family such as a wider routed or multi-branch encoder rather than continuing local sweeps."]}
