research/history_archive/06_20260320_183226/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Both encoder-capacity families tried so far are far behind the K=128 TopK anchor, so the next coherent probe is a different sparse activation mechanism rather than more mixing capacity; `jumprelu` may improve feature selection quality by learning per-latent activation thresholds.","summary":"Run a proxy `jumprelu` experiment at K=128 with the same Adam/LR settings as the current TopK anchor to test whether learnable thresholding can materially improve reconstruction quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is still a first-pass family probe, and the default threshold/bandwidth settings may be poorly tuned. If the result is weak, that may mean either the family is unpromising here or that it needs a stabilization pass before a real comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`mixture_topk` improved over `factorized_topk` but remained far behind the mainline K=128 TopK anchor, so extra encoder mixture capacity alone is not closing the quality gap.","Continue exploring qualitatively different architecture families at fixed K=128 until one shows a real path below the 0.211975 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` is competitive in proxy, follow with a stabilization round on its threshold and bandwidth parameters before promotion.","If `jumprelu` is also clearly worse than TopK, move to another qualitatively different family such as `gated` or a new multi-branch sparse encoder.","If `jumprelu` is quality-promising but unstable, keep the family incubating and tune its activation hyperparameters rather than discarding it immediately."]}
