research/history_archive/06_20260320_183226/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Orthogonality regularization did not improve the K=128 TopK anchor, so the next within-family quality intervention is to train the K=128 model to remain reconstructive under slightly smaller nested supports; a lightly weighted matryoshka objective may sharpen feature ranking and improve full-K FVU.","summary":"Run a proxy TopK experiment at K=128 with Adam and a mild matryoshka loss over smaller nested K values to test whether rank-aware training can beat the current TopK baseline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This still relies on the current TopK family, so the upside may be limited. If the proxy remains flat or worse, that is a stronger signal that incremental TopK regularization is not enough and the next step should be a more substantial architecture implementation rather than another small training tweak.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"MATRYOSHKA_KS","value":"96,64"},{"key":"MATRYOSHKA_WEIGHTS","value":"0.25,0.125"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["TopK + orthogonality regularization failed to improve proxy quality at K=128, so simple decoder-basis regularization is not the missing ingredient.","Continue K=128 quality work with interventions aimed at better latent ranking or allocation rather than rewarding lower-K endpoints directly."],"next_hypotheses":["If TopK + matryoshka improves proxy quality, promote it and tune the nested K set or weights while keeping evaluation focused on K=128 quality.","If TopK + matryoshka is neutral or worse, stop incremental TopK regularizer search and implement a genuinely new architecture family with a sharper allocation mechanism.","If the matryoshka run helps quality but hurts throughput, keep it as a quality lead and follow with a targeted cost/perf cleanup later."]}
