research/history_archive/06_20260320_183226/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The new K=128 TopK+Adam anchor at FVU 0.211975 is strong enough to stop local optimizer tinkering for now; a more expressive nonlinear encoder is the next plausible path toward a materially lower FVU, so `factorized_topk` should be tested at the same K=128 anchor settings.","summary":"Run a proxy `factorized_topk` experiment at K=128 with the same Adam/LR settings as the current TopK anchor to test whether the added hidden mixing stage can beat the 0.211975 full-baseline trajectory on quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This introduces a new architecture family, so the first proxy result may underperform or show extra compute cost. If it is only marginally better than TopK, it still may not justify promotion given the aggressive goal of roughly halving the current baseline FVU.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["A trustworthy K=128 quality anchor now exists: full TopK+Adam at FVU 0.2119751125574112.","With the anchor established and still far from the aggressive target, bias subsequent rounds toward architecture exploration rather than more local TopK retuning."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` shows materially better proxy FVU at K=128, promote it and then tune its encoder width or related family-specific capacity.","If `factorized_topk` is neutral or worse, try another expressive encoder family such as `mixture_topk` rather than returning immediately to smaller-K search.","If the new family is quality-promising but noticeably slower, treat that as a performance-fix follow-up instead of an immediate architectural rejection."]}
