research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At fixed K=128, a Hadamard-rotated JumpReLU encoder with a nontrivial learned threshold will suppress weak nuisance activations before top-k selection, improving support precision enough to beat the rotated topk anchor on proxy FVU.","summary":"Run a proxy prototype for a rotated JumpReLU family at K=128. This keeps the quality-first anchor fixed while testing whether thresholded sparse activation can materially outperform rotated topk, instead of spending another round on a likely weak local topk sweep.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"rotated_jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This respects the fixed execution layer and uses only env overrides against an already-supported architecture family. It is a single coherent quality-first bet at K=128, which matches the program's guidance to escalate from modest rotated-topk gains into architecture exploration. The main risk is threshold miscalibration: if the initial threshold is too low JumpReLU may collapse toward topk, while if it is too high it may over-prune useful features. Proxy is the right place to test viability before any family-specific stabilization.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.02"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 2 escalates from modest rotated-topk improvement into a new encoder family rather than continuing local topk tuning.","The current codebase already supports JumpReLU through env overrides, so this prototype can be tested without touching the execution layer.","No operator_hints were present in structured context for this round."],"next_hypotheses":["If rotated JumpReLU shows promising proxy FVU but unstable optimization, keep the family alive with an optimizer-focused stabilization pass such as Adam or LR retuning.","If rotated JumpReLU improves quality but is still far from the aggressive target, sweep its threshold and bandwidth as the next family-specific stabilization step.","If rotated JumpReLU fails to show useful quality signal, move to a different encoder family with stronger routing expressivity rather than returning to weak local topk search."]}
