research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0024.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` has now improved the full frontier at both K=128 and K=64, so the next clean move is to change only K again and test whether the family also strengthens the smallest currently active Pareto point. A proxy K=32 run under the same EF=32 signum recipe will show whether the gated residual selector is a general frontier improvement rather than only a medium/high-K gain.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=32 while holding EF=32, signum, LR=1.6e-3, and AUXK_ALPHA=0 fixed. This directly tests whether the new family can replace `lowrank_residual` across the full current Pareto set by improving the smallest-K point as well.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round to one primary variable, `k`, and follows the family-specific stabilization sequence opened by the successful K=128 and K=64 full results. It is the highest-value next check because it can either complete a coherent frontier takeover for the family or cleanly bound where its gains stop.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 24 tests `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=32 after full wins at K=128 and K=64 under the shared EF=32 signum recipe.","This is the next stabilization step needed to determine whether `lowrank_gated_residual` can become the mainline family across the whole current Pareto frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` improves proxy FVU at K=32, promote it to full and treat the family as the leading mainline across K={32,64,128}.","If K=32 is flat or worse, keep `lowrank_gated_residual` as the better family for K>=64 and consider a single-variable internal stabilization move such as `AUXK_ALPHA` within this family.","If K=32 quality is promising but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with a narrow `code_fix` performance pass instead of concluding against the architecture."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0070.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` dominates from `K=2` to `K=16` but loses at `K=1`, while `lowrank_two_stage_residual` still owns the `K=1` endpoint. A hybrid that adds a soft codebook coarse residual projection before the proven two-stage low-rank residual refinement may recover the `K=1` slot without giving up the family’s low-K gains.","summary":"Added and smoke-tested a new architecture, `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, then propose one architecture experiment at `K=1` with the existing winning low-K recipe otherwise fixed.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single-hypothesis architecture step targeted exactly at the remaining uncovered endpoint. It reuses two validated ingredients already showing complementary strengths in this repo and was integration-smoke-tested on the exact launch target `K=1, EF=12`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"1"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 70 introduces `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, a new prototype that combines the soft codebook coarse residual projection with the existing low-rank two-stage residual refinement.","Integration chain completed for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`: config whitelist + `_get_sae_class()` dispatch + class implementation in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`.","Exact smoke test passed for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=1, EF=12` on the concrete dispatched architecture class (`integration_smoke: OK ... cuda`).","Round 70 should test whether this hybrid can beat the current `K=1` frontier anchor (`lowrank_two_stage_residual`, FVU `0.17282412946224213`) while keeping the stronger `LR=3.2e-3` recipe that benefited the soft-codebook family across `K=2-16`."],"next_hypotheses":["If the hybrid wins at `K=1`, test `K=2` to see whether it can subsume the current `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` low-K band.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=1`, consider one confirmatory rerun before deciding whether the deficit is architectural or noise.","If it clearly loses at `K=1`, retain `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` for `K=2-16`, keep `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=1`, and resume a different new-family search for the endpoint."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
