research/history_archive/06_20260320_183226/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The first-step timeout is caused by serialized DDP startup for local artifacts rather than by the K=128 TopK/Adam configuration itself; allowing both ranks to load the local model and dataset in parallel should get the proxy run to first metrics.","summary":"Retry the same K=128 TopK Adam anchor after a narrow startup fix in `sparsify/__main__.py` that skips unnecessary rank-by-rank artifact loading when the model and dataset paths are local.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"run_stability","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This targets startup latency only, so it may not help if the watchdog is being tripped by a different pre-step bottleneck such as dataset shuffling or hook initialization. The quality hypothesis itself remains untested until the run reaches metrics.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/__main__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 1 crash still has no usable FVU signal; treat it as startup-path failure, not as evidence against TopK or Adam.","Local DDP artifact loading was serialized in sparsify/__main__.py; this round parallelizes local-path startup across ranks to reduce first-step latency."],"next_hypotheses":["If the retry reaches metrics, resume K=128 quality work before considering any lower-K point.","If startup still times out, inspect dataset shuffle/select ordering and other pre-step costs in the local artifact path.","If the run succeeds but Adam does not materially improve K=128 quality, escalate to a new encoder family rather than continuing local optimizer search."]}
