research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Twelve no-improve rounds indicate that the current search direction is fundamentally flawed, and the latest alternative sparse-allocation families still sit far behind the frontier. The next coherent architecture move is to test conditionalized dictionaries rather than another global-allocation variant: add `bucketed_topk`, which routes samples between separate low-norm and high-norm dictionaries before TopK selection. If the activation distribution is multi-regime rather than unimodal, specializing dictionaries by sample norm could improve reconstruction quality without changing the fixed execution layer.","summary":"Add a new `bucketed_topk` family under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe that tests conditional mixture-of-dictionaries behavior instead of more tuning on fixed or batch-global support allocation.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round changes one core variable only, the architecture, and keeps all launcher and metric semantics fixed. The implementation is confined to `sparsify/`, registers through the existing validation/factory path, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed for the new conditional dictionary route.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `bucketed_topk`, a conditional dictionary architecture that mixes separate low-norm and high-norm encoder branches before TopK selection.","Registered `bucketed_topk` in the existing architecture validation and factory paths under `sparsify/` only.","Local smoke test passed for `bucketed_topk` forward/backward execution, confirming the new route is trainable under the current codebase."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, keep the family alive and promote it to full before any local tuning.","If `bucketed_topk` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented `code_fix` on the conditional routing path rather than discarding the family immediately.","If `bucketed_topk` remains clearly behind, archive norm-bucketed conditional dictionaries and pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
