research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed at `K=16` and reducing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 12 to 8 will test whether this family can add a lower-cost non-dominated point without giving up too much FVU.","summary":"Use a parameter-only probe on the existing `lowrank_two_stage_residual` family at `K=16`, changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` to `8` while pinning `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. The low-K tail has already been mapped from `K=32` down to `K=1`, so the next clean frontier question is whether the same family can trade some reconstruction quality for a meaningfully smaller model at a proven useful K.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_ef","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This avoids the prior policy-rejected code-plus-architecture move, preserves strict variable isolation with `primary_variable=expansion_factor`, and probes the remaining frontier dimension on a stable family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 9 shifts from the completed K sweep to an EF sweep on the same family, using `K=16` as the anchor and changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR`.","The previous routed-family proposal was policy-rejected because it coupled code editing with an architecture change, so the next step should stay parameter-only and isolate a single frontier dimension."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16, EF=8` stays competitive, continue to `K=24, EF=8` or `K=8, EF=8` to map the lower-EF lane.","If `EF=8` degrades too much at `K=16`, keep `EF=12` for this family and revisit architecture changes only after a clean code-only integration plan.","If `EF=8` is borderline but promising, test `EF=10` at the same `K=16` to refine the cost-quality knee."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
