research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0081.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`residual_vq_topk` still has not produced a real low-K signal because the prototype failed at the implementation layer before training, so the next move is one more narrow code-fix pass to make the existing `K=32`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` experiment runnable without changing its design.","summary":"Do a repair-focused pass on the existing `residual_vq_topk` prototype under `sparsify/` so the original proxy target can actually launch and survive sanity/startup. Keep the family, tier, and override set fixed; only patch the concrete implementation blocker.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"residual_vq_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the crash-repair-first rule and does not spend another round on parameter churn. The prototype has not earned a quality verdict yet because it has not run successfully, so one more narrow repair attempt is more informative than abandoning or redesigning it immediately.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`residual_vq_topk` remains an implementation-blocked prototype rather than a judged architecture result until it completes a real run.","Keep repair scope narrow and confined to startup/sanity compatibility for the existing experiment target; do not redesign the family during repair.","If the next repair succeeds and the run completes, judge the family on quality; if it fails again with a new concrete blocker, continue only with another narrowly scoped repair."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq_topk` launches and completes, evaluate whether the discrete coarse-plus-residual framing is competitive enough to keep incubating at low K.","If a new concrete forward/backward or DDP compatibility error appears, do one more narrow repair pass with the same experiment target rather than changing architecture or overrides.","If the repaired prototype runs cleanly but is clearly weak, archive `residual_vq_topk` on quality grounds and pivot to a different fundamentally different family."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0066.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"In crash-recovery mode, the safest informative move is to stay on the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` small-EF recipe and step K down from the last stable `K=64` probe to `K=56`, testing whether a lower-K point can still run cleanly while improving the low-K map.","summary":"Use the current best working family and shared stable optimizer/LR recipe, keep `EF=8` fixed, and change only `K` from the last stable small-EF recovery point to `56`. This preserves stability-first behavior while continuing the required lower-K exploration without touching code.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery constraints exactly: no code edits, same known-good family, one minor parameter change, and a lower-K move from the last clean run. The risk is another weak proxy result, but it should restore a stable signal before any further architecture work.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"56"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 66 is constrained by crash-recovery mode, so it reverts to the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` family with no code changes.","This recovery probe keeps the stable small-EF recipe fixed and changes only `K` from the prior stable `K=64` point down to `K=56` to continue lower-K mapping conservatively.","If this run is stable, use it as the new recovery anchor before resuming broader architecture exploration; if it crashes, treat the issue as broader runtime instability rather than an architecture conclusion."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, `EF=8` runs cleanly, continue the recovery sweep to a nearby lower K such as `K=48` before changing architecture again.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, `EF=8` crashes despite being a known working family, stay in stability-first mode and try an even more conservative parameter-only recovery move rather than any code or architecture change."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0248.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u5355\u6837\u672c\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u7684\u6253\u5206\u4e0e\u9009\u62e9\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r247 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=32`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u5df2\u786e\u8ba4 `K=96 -> 64` \u4ec5\u5e26\u6765\u6709\u9650 FVU \u9000\u5316\u540e\uff0c\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u628a\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u538b\u5230\u7ea6 0.08x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u65f6\uff0cFVU \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u7ef4\u6301\u5728\u540c\u4e00\u91cf\u7ea7\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u786e\u5b9a\u8fd9\u6761\u8d85\u4f4e\u6210\u672c factorized scorer \u652f\u7ebf\u7684\u6700\u5de6\u53ef\u7528\u8fb9\u754c\u3002",
