research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0110.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After eleven non-improving rounds, the next worthwhile move is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; a plain low-rank gated residual model may outperform the recent codebook, VQ, and adaptive-budget branches at K=24 by using a simpler support-selection mechanism on top of the proven low-rank trunk.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the most recent fundamentally different branches (`lowrank_residual_vq`, `adaptive_budget_topk`, `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual`) all lost clearly at `K=24`. The next clean test should stay on the valuable smaller-K anchor but switch to another distinct mechanism: run `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=24` with the stable EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe. This isolates architecture alone and checks whether a simpler gated selector can recover the mid-K lane better than the more elaborate recent branches.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than tuning within a losing branch, keeps K in the allowed set, and targets a meaningful frontier slot. The risk is that older-budget evidence for `lowrank_gated_residual` at nearby K was only modest, but it is still a more defensible next mechanism than continuing codebook or adaptive-budget variants after repeated failures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` also lost clearly at `K=24`, dynamic-budget routing looks unpromising for the current EF=12 mid-K lane.","Round 110 should probe `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as another fundamentally different support-selection mechanism.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result remains attributable to architecture alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the simpler gated mechanism scales across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to codebook or adaptive-budget tweaks.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
