research/history_archive/03_20260320_180114/logs/agent_action_0001.json:1:{"command":"stop","hypothesis":"Blocked: the local execution tool is failing before any repository inspection, so I cannot read `research/program.md` or verify the current `sparsify/` architecture state safely.","summary":"I could not begin a coherent research round because every local command failed immediately with `bwrap: Unknown option --argv0`. That prevents the required read of `research/program.md` and any codebase inspection, so proposing or editing an SAE family would be guesswork.","change_type":"no_change","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the safest outcome under the tooling failure. The round rules require reading `research/program.md` before deciding, and I could not satisfy that prerequisite.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Local command execution is currently broken with `bwrap: Unknown option --argv0`, blocking required repository inspection."],"next_hypotheses":["Once command execution works, first read `research/program.md` and inspect existing `sparsify/` families before choosing a single quality-first hypothesis.","Bias toward establishing a strong K=128 quality anchor or introducing a new encoder family only after repository inspection confirms the current baseline and search space."]}
