research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0153.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the plain non-bucketed two-stage soft-codebook family also lost at `K=24`, the next severe-stagnation move should be another fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more recipe tuning. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining structurally distinct soft-codebook variant for this slot because grouped competition changes capacity allocation more materially than scalar hyperparameters and may produce a better small-K Pareto tradeoff under the fixed EF=16 recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current stable recipe. This follows policy guidance to stop minor tweaks after prolonged stagnation, keeps the probe on a valuable smaller-K slot, and tests whether grouped selection can outperform both the exhausted bucketed backbone and the weaker plain two-stage variant in the current EF=16 lane.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean single-variable architecture test using an already registered family. The main risk is that grouped competition may again be too restrictive, but that is still a more policy-consistent next action than continuing optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after they both failed. `K=24` remains the highest-value unclaimed smaller-K slot where a non-dominated tradeoff would still matter even without beating the `K=32` anchor on absolute FVU.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 153 continues severe-stagnation recovery by trying another fundamentally different existing architecture at `K=24, EF=16` after plain `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` also failed to open a new frontier point.","`lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is selected because grouping changes support allocation more materially than recent scalar recipe tweaks while staying within the existing registered family set.","Keep the recipe pinned to signum + `LR=3.2e-3` + no Hadamard so attribution stays on the grouped architecture rather than optimizer or preprocessing drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to map whether grouping improves the low-K tradeoff curve further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test another structurally distinct existing family such as `lowrank_residual_vq` or `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar tuning.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, treat grouped soft-codebook routing as noncompetitive in the current EF=16 small-K lane and move to the next fundamentally different existing architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0244.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1bfactorized scorer \u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u5355\u6837\u672c\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u7684\u6253\u5206\u94fe\u8def\uff0cdecoder \u7aef\u4ecd\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r242 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `K=96`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u7ea6 0.38x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u4f4d\u7f6e\uff0c\u7528\u66f4\u77ed\u7684\u4f4e\u79e9 scorer \u94fe\u8def\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u6bd4 `topk@K96` \u7684 FVU=0.2219 \u7ed9\u51fa\u66f4\u597d\u7684\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500 Pareto \u6743\u8861\u3002",
