research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"On the current best frontier point `lowrank_two_stage_residual, K=32, EF=12`, increasing only the learning rate from `1.6e-3` to the untested `3.2e-3` may improve signum optimization enough to recover or beat the anchor after the lower-LR sweep underperformed.","summary":"Run the opposite-direction LR sweep on the current best fixed recipe, holding architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and `AUXK_ALPHA` constant while changing only `LR` to `3.2e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This matches the exploitation policy and the immediate follow-up implied by round 15: one parameter changes, no new family, no EF move, and the test stays on the strongest anchor. The lower-LR trial was clearly worse, so the highest-information next step is the opposite LR direction before moving on to aux sweeps.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 16 continues exploitation on the `K=32, EF=12` anchor by testing the opposite LR direction after `4e-4` substantially worsened FVU.","This isolates whether the anchor prefers a more aggressive signum step size rather than a more conservative one before spending more rounds on aux sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=3.2e-3` improves the `K=32` anchor, finish the LR sweep with `2e-4` only if needed for confirmation; otherwise keep the better LR as the new anchor recipe.","If `LR=3.2e-3` is also worse, treat the anchor as LR-stable around `1.6e-3` and shift the next isolated exploitation round to `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` at the same fixed recipe.","If the result is close to baseline but not better, prioritize aux exploration over further LR tuning because both LR directions will have been probed without a frontier gain."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
