research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0119.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At K=16, the best next chance for a non-dominated smaller-K point is a fundamentally different support mechanism on the strong soft-codebook backbone. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` was relatively competitive at K=24, so it may outperform the current K=16 frontier by using gated selection after soft codebook residualization.","summary":"Severe stagnation has reached 20 non-improving rounds, so another minor tweak is not justified. The latest new-family probes around stage splits, routing, bucketing, and whitening on the two-stage soft-codebook backbone have all failed, so the next move should be a fundamentally different existing architecture rather than another close variant. The strongest remaining candidate is `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` at the more valuable smaller-K slot `K=16` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This keeps one hypothesis and avoids another code-edit branch after several unsuccessful new-family integrations. The main risk is that the gated soft-codebook family may remain slightly behind the routed/two-stage incumbents, but its K=24 result was competitive enough that K=16 is a credible smaller-K probe.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 119 should satisfy severe-stagnation policy with a fundamentally different architecture, but use an already integrated family instead of opening another new code path immediately.","`lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` was reasonably competitive at K=24, so K=16 is the highest-value smaller-K probe for this family under the fixed recipe.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone at the frontier-relevant K=16 slot."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at K=16, follow with K=24 confirmation only if needed to map whether the gain persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at K=16, continue severe-stagnation search with another fundamentally different existing family rather than more soft-codebook two-stage variants.","If it is close but noisy at K=16, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
