research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/logs/agent_action_0008.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`K=96` established a valid smaller-support `topk` point without crashing, so the next single-question K-stage move is to measure whether the cost-quality slope stays acceptable when support is cut more materially. Dropping from `K=96` to `K=64` on the same tuned signum recipe will show whether LUTurbo can gain a more meaningful selection-cost reduction before reconstruction degrades too sharply.","summary":"Keep the `topk` mainline recipe fixed at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and change only `K` from `96` to `64`. This continues the K-stage mapping in the same family and answers one concrete question: whether the first nontrivial support cut beyond `K=96` still yields an acceptable Pareto tradeoff for deployment-oriented cost reduction.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This respects the single-variable rule and stays on the active family while extending the K frontier in the prescribed final stage. The main risk is that `K=64` may fall off the quality cliff, so the result should be judged by the whole curve and by whether the extra support reduction is large enough to justify any observed FVU loss.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`topk` now has two EF=12 frontier anchors under the tuned signum recipe: `K=128` at `FVU=0.4522051215171814` and `K=96` at `FVU=0.4886302351951599`.","Round 8 continues the K stage by testing `K=64` under the same `topk` signum recipe to estimate whether a larger support reduction can still be deployment-viable.","Interpret this round by both curve shape and Pareto value: even if FVU worsens, `K=64` may still matter if degradation is gradual rather than cliff-like."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=64` remains reasonably close to the `K=96` point, continue to `K=32` on the same recipe to map the low-K slope.","If `K=64` shows a sharp quality cliff, stop forcing lower K on plain `topk` and treat new family search as the more promising route for LUTurbo cost reduction.","If `K=64` is borderline, compare its curve shape against `K=96` to decide whether the lower-K regime deserves an LR retune before abandoning it."],"primary_variable":"k"}
