research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0099.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has already shown strong gains at K=16, 64, 96, and 128, and its earlier K=32 result was slightly better than the current listed K=32 frontier anchor. A clean confirmatory rerun at K=32 under the pinned winning recipe is the highest-value next step because it can add a more valuable smaller-K non-dominated point while avoiding another policy-rejected code edit.","summary":"Run one parameter-only confirmation experiment at K=32 with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This directly tests whether the routed family should also own the K=32 frontier slot under the same recipe that already wins at K=16 and the higher-K anchors.","change_type":"param_only","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This stays within the fixed execution layer and uses only allowed env overrides after the previous code-edit round was policy-rejected. The hypothesis is narrow and high-value: verify whether routing improves the important mid-K anchor at K=32 under an otherwise frozen recipe. The main risk is that the prior K=32 routed win was noise and the plain two-stage soft-codebook model remains slightly better there.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 98's code-edit hypothesis was policy-rejected, so round 99 should return to env-only experiments.","The most valuable unresolved frontier question is whether the routed soft-codebook family also owns the K=32 EF=12 slot under the pinned winning recipe.","A K=32 routed confirmation would extend the routed family farther down the Pareto frontier and strengthen it as the main EF=12 backbone."],"next_hypotheses":["If routed wins at K=32, run the same fixed recipe at K=24 to test whether the routed advantage extends one more step into the smaller-K regime.","If routed is very close but does not win at K=32, keep plain `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=32 and shift follow-up effort to K=24 or K=64 cleanup instead of more K=32 repeats.","If routed clearly loses at K=32, conclude that the routed advantage starts above this band and keep the family focused on K>=64 plus the established K=16 slot."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has now improved both `K=8` and `K=16`, so the next highest-value test is whether the same routing advantage extends to `K=24`, where the current frontier is still owned by the non-routed variant.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=24` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This cleanly maps whether the new family is becoming the dominant low/mid-K backbone rather than a narrow win at only `K=8` and `K=16`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is a straightforward exploitation step with a single changed dimension (`K`). It directly follows the observed frontier gains and avoids unnecessary code churn. The main risk is that routing helps only in tighter-budget regimes and may become neutral or harmful by `K=24`, but that is precisely what this run will resolve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["r93 should extend the routed soft-codebook family sweep to `K=24` after frontier wins at `K=8` and `K=16`.","Keep the recipe fixed and change only `K` so the result cleanly measures whether routing remains helpful in the mid-K regime.","A `K=24` win would strongly suggest the routed soft-codebook family is the new EF=12 backbone across multiple frontier slots."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=24`, test it at `K=32` under the same recipe to see whether routing can displace the current high end of the EF=12 frontier as well.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=24`, consider a small routed-temperature adjustment as the first targeted tuning step for this family.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, conclude that the routed advantage likely tops out by `K=16` and focus future routed-family work on low-K slots only."],"primary_variable":"k"}
