research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`adam` at the signum-tuned LR regressed enough that the current `topk` mainline should revert to the stronger `signum` anchor and advance to the next stage in the recommended order: loss shaping. Under the now-tuned `signum` regime, the inherited `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` auxiliary pressure may be over-regularizing support usage, so removing it could improve reconstruction curve shape and final FVU at `K=128` without changing LUTurbo compatibility.","summary":"Keep the `topk` mainline anchor fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, and change only the auxiliary-loss setting by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This asks one clean question after the optimizer check failed: whether the tuned signum topk recipe now works better without auxiliary sparsity shaping.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the family fixed, respects the single-variable rule, and moves to the next recommended stage after `adam` failed to beat the signum anchor. The main risk is that aux removal can improve early FVU while harming late utilization, so this run should be judged by the whole curve and support behavior rather than the final scalar alone.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`adam` at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.0e-3` underperformed the signum anchor (`0.46458443999290466` vs `0.4522051215171814`), so `signum` remains the current optimizer winner for topk mainline.","Round 6 returns to the best signum anchor and starts the loss/preprocess stage with a single-variable probe on `AUXK_ALPHA`.","Evaluate this run by curve shape and late behavior as well as final FVU: if aux-free training descends faster early but stalls or destabilizes late, keep the original aux loss."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the curve and final FVU, keep the aux-free signum recipe as the new topk anchor before considering preprocessing.","If aux removal hurts late behavior or final FVU, restore `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` and test a preprocessing change such as Hadamard only if the curve suggests representation conditioning is the next bottleneck.","If the loss/preprocess stage yields no gain, move to the K stage next and test whether a smaller `K` can offer a better LUTurbo tradeoff under the strongest confirmed topk recipe."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
