research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After 20 no-improve rounds and repeated failures from routed, gated, discrete, bucketed, and low-rank variants at `K=24`, the next severe-stagnation move should reset to the simplest fundamentally different baseline rather than layering on more mechanism. Plain `topk` at `K=24, EF=12` may outperform the recent complex branches by avoiding their optimization overhead and support-allocation pathologies, potentially recovering a cleaner mid-K Pareto point.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows severe-stagnation policy by making an architecture-only jump away from the recent failed mechanisms and re-establishing whether the plain sparse-coding baseline is stronger than the accumulated complex alternatives at the frontier-relevant mid-K slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"baseline_recheck","self_review":"I avoided more support-selection or low-rank refinements because policy says minor tweaks are exhausted, and the recent complex families all lost badly at `K=24`. Rechecking plain `topk` is a defensible fundamentally different move: it strips away auxiliary architectural assumptions and gives a clean reference point under the same pinned recipe.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 continues severe-stagnation recovery by resetting to plain `topk` at `K=24` after multiple more complex families failed badly in the same slot.","Keep the run pinned at `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so architecture is the only primary variable.","`topk` tests whether the mid-K frontier is better served by the simplest sparse coding baseline than by the recent routed, gated, bucketed, discrete, and low-rank mechanisms."],"next_hypotheses":["If `topk` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test it at K=16 to see whether the simpler baseline is stronger under tighter sparsity.","If `topk` clearly loses at K=24, retire the plain-baseline reset and move to another genuinely different built-in family rather than any scalar sweep.","If `topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the simpler architecture generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
