research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After hard failures from branch-mixing, thresholded sparsity, staged residual coding, and batch-level budget allocation, a discrete coarse-code baseline is the next fundamentally different mechanism worth testing: `residual_vq` at `K=24, EF=12` may recover a better mid-K tradeoff by handling shared structure with a learned codebook before sparse residual correction.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `residual_vq` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This matches the severe-stagnation policy by continuing the search over genuinely different built-in families rather than any further scalar tweak.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, K, and EF sweeps because 11 no-improve rounds means minor tuning is exhausted. I also kept K fixed at 24 for a clean read against the current frontier slot while moving to a substantially different discrete-reconstruction family.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 46 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a codebook-based family after `multi_branch_gated`, `jumprelu`, `two_stage_residual`, and `batch_topk` all failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with every recipe field pinned explicitly.","`residual_vq` tests a qualitatively different coarse-plus-residual mechanism than the recent continuous sparse-coding families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test `two_code_residual_vq` at the same K to see whether a deeper discrete coarse stage helps.","If `residual_vq` clearly loses at K=24, reject this codebook branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `factorized_topk` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `residual_vq` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=16` missed the current frontier by only a small margin, so the failure may be band-specific rather than a clean rejection of the family at `EF=12`. Increasing only `K` from `16` to `24` under the same settled recipe tests whether gating becomes beneficial in the adjacent mid-K regime and can beat the current `K=24` `lowrank_two_stage_residual` point.","summary":"Run a pure-`K` follow-up on `lowrank_gated_residual` by keeping architecture, expansion factor, optimizer, learning rate, and aux fixed to the round-36 recipe and changing only `K` from `16` to `24`. This checks whether the gated branch is competitive in the nearby transition band before abandoning the family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the explicit guidance for a close-but-worse architecture result: test one adjacent `K` before rejecting the family. It changes exactly one primary variable relative to round 36, keeps the comparison controlled, and probes a frontier-relevant slot where slightly higher support may let the gate branch pay off.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 37 treats the round-36 `lowrank_gated_residual` result at `K=16` as a close miss rather than an immediate rejection and tests one adjacent `K` under the same controlled recipe.","The goal is to determine whether gating helps specifically in the `K=24, EF=12` transition band before closing this family and moving on to another substantial architecture branch."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` wins at `K=24`, continue the same controlled family comparison at `K=32` or rerun once for confirmation before any scalar sweep.","If it is again close but slightly worse at `K=24`, reject the family at `EF=12` and open a different substantial architecture branch.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, stop exploring this family in the low-EF lane and pivot to another materially different architecture rather than minor tweaks."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0160.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `lowrank_two_stage_residual` also failed at `K=24, EF=16`, the severe-stagnation policy still points to another fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more recipe tuning. `lowrank_residual` is the strongest remaining low-K candidate because it removes the second-stage composition entirely and previously showed the best ultra-low-K robustness, so its simpler trunk-plus-residual path may scale more gracefully to the current `K=24, EF=16` slot than the more structured two-stage variants.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current signum baseline. This continues the severe-stagnation recovery with a materially different existing family, targets a valuable smaller-K slot where a non-dominated point still matters, and avoids returning to minor optimizer or preprocessing tweaks that have not worked.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean one-variable architecture probe and fits the current policy better than more Adam retuning or another preprocessing pass. The risk is that `lowrank_residual` may need smaller K to shine, but it still offers a meaningfully different inductive bias from the recently failed two-stage, multi-branch, gating, VQ, and soft-codebook families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 160 continues severe-stagnation architecture search after `lowrank_two_stage_residual` also failed to open a new `K=24, EF=16` frontier point.","Hypothesis: `lowrank_residual` is the next most informative fundamentally different low-K family because its simpler single-stage low-rank residual path may recover a better small-K tradeoff than the recently exhausted multi-stage and structured-selection variants under the fixed modern signum recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to test whether its simpler inductive bias helps further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test another fundamentally different existing family at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar recipe tweaks.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, deprioritize plain low-rank residual coding in the current EF=16 regime and continue severe-stagnation search with the next distinct architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0101.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A small auxiliary loss at `K=32` was slightly worse than the incumbent but close enough that aux tuning is not yet settled for the plain two-stage soft-codebook family. The remaining informative single-variable follow-up is to test a stronger `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` at the same `K=32` anchor and determine whether higher dead-feature pressure improves utilization enough to beat the current frontier.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=32` with `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.2e-3` fixed while changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.01` to `0.0625`. Success criterion: beat the current `K=32` frontier anchor FVU (`0.08386963605880737`) and resolve whether aux tuning has any remaining value for the non-routed mid-K recipe.","change_type":"param_only","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This follows the precommitted next step from round 100 and keeps strict one-variable isolation at a frontier-relevant anchor. The main risk is that stronger aux pressure will further degrade FVU, but that would cleanly close the aux-tuning branch and justify moving on to a different scalar or family next round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 showed `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` at `K=32` was close but still slightly worse than the incumbent `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` anchor.","Round 101 should test the remaining stronger aux setting at the same `K=32` anchor before abandoning aux tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","Keep all recipe fields fixed except `AUXK_ALPHA` so the result cleanly answers whether stronger dead-feature pressure helps the plain soft-codebook mid-K lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` wins at `K=32`, propagate that aux setting to `K=24` under the same fixed recipe to test whether the gain generalizes.","If it is still close but behind at `K=32`, settle `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` as the best plain-family mid-K recipe and switch the next cleanup round to an LR sweep.","If it clearly loses at `K=32`, conclude that aux tuning is exhausted for this anchor and move the next round to a different single-variable dimension such as learning rate or a new family."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
