research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0109_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The plain `adaptive_budget_topk` failure suggests dynamic support allocation needs a stronger representational backbone, not that the mechanism is useless; adding adaptive-budget selection on top of the proven low-rank residual trunk may produce a better K=24 tradeoff than either plain adaptive-budget or the recent soft-codebook branches.","summary":"Repaired the engineering blocker for `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` without changing the planned experiment. Added the architecture string to the whitelist in `sparsify/config.py`, added factory dispatch in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`, and implemented `LowRankAdaptiveBudgetResidualSparseCoder` by combining the existing low-rank residual trunk with the existing adaptive-budget quota logic. Verified the exact target with an instantiate/forward/backward smoke test at `(architecture=lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual, K=24, EF=12)`, which passed on CUDA. The original round-109 experiment can now run unchanged.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stayed within `sparsify/` only and preserved the original family and override contract exactly. The prior failure was purely a registration-chain blocker; that chain is now closed and the exact smoke target passed, so the next run should measure the architecture rather than fail at parse/dispatch time.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repaired `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` registration and implementation under `sparsify/`: whitelist entry, factory dispatch, and concrete class now exist.","Exact smoke test passed for `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` at `(K=24, EF=12)` with instantiate, forward, and backward on CUDA.","Round 109 repair attempt 1 resolved an `Unknown architecture` blocker, so the original experiment should now be rerun unchanged to evaluate the family scientifically."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, run the same fixed recipe at `K=16` or `K=32` to map whether the gain is localized or broad across the mid/low-K band.","If it runs cleanly but clearly loses at `K=24`, treat dynamic-budget routing as unpromising even with a strong low-rank backbone and move to a different mechanism entirely.","If the full run now fails with a new runtime or autograd issue, repair that new blocker before drawing any scientific conclusion about the architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
