research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0115.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At K=24, the current two-stage soft-codebook backbone may be wasting scarce support by splitting K evenly across stages. A new `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` family that allocates more of K to the first sparse pass and keeps a smaller refinement pass could beat the K=24 anchor by using the strongest existing backbone but changing the stage budget structurally for the small-K regime.","summary":"Severe stagnation is now at 16 non-improving rounds, so this round should not do another scalar tweak or reuse another recently losing built-in family. The best next move is a fundamentally different architecture edit on the strongest current backbone: add an asymmetric two-stage soft-codebook variant under `sparsify/` and test it directly at the frontier-relevant K=24 slot with the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps one hypothesis and changes architecture only. It is bolder than another built-in retry but still disciplined because it starts from the current winning family rather than inventing a disconnected mechanism. Main risk: asymmetry may simply reduce second-stage correction capacity and underperform the symmetric split, but that is precisely the structural question worth testing under severe stagnation.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 115 should satisfy severe-stagnation policy by introducing a genuinely new architecture instead of another param-only retry after the catastrophic `whitened_lowrank_residual` miss.","Implement `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as a variant of the existing two-stage soft-codebook family with an intentionally uneven stage budget so more of K is spent in stage 1 and less in stage 2.","Complete the full registration chain before training: add the exact architecture string to `valid_archs`, dispatch it in `_get_sae_class()`, implement the concrete class in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`, then run the exact instantiate/forward/backward smoke test at `(architecture=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=24, EF=12)`.","Keep the launch contract minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone at K=24."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at K=24, follow with K=16 to test whether asymmetric budget allocation helps even more under tighter sparsity.","If it clearly loses at K=24, continue severe-stagnation search with another structurally different new family rather than returning to selector, routing, or whitening tweaks.","If the exact smoke test passes but the full run fails, summarize the new blocker precisely and repair that architecture-specific issue before judging the family scientifically."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0247.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u5355\u6837\u672c\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u7684\u6253\u5206\u4e0e\u9009\u62e9\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r246 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=64`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u5df2\u786e\u8ba4\u53ef\u5f62\u6210 0.14x \u5de6\u7aef\u70b9\u4e4b\u540e\uff0c\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u628a\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u538b\u4f4e\u5230\u66f4\u5de6\u4fa7\u65f6\uff0cFVU \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u57fa\u672c\u7ef4\u6301\u5728\u540c\u4e00\u91cf\u7ea7\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u8865\u51fa\u66f4\u5b8c\u6574\u7684\u8d85\u4f4e\u6210\u672c Pareto \u5de6\u8fb9\u754c\u3002",
