research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent failures suggest the extra low-rank/gating structure may be hurting rather than helping, so a simpler coarse-to-fine residual stack may recover mid-K quality: `two_stage_residual` at `K=24, EF=12` could outperform the recent non-lowrank misses and potentially challenge the current `K=24` frontier point without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `two_stage_residual` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by trying another fundamentally different built-in architecture and avoids any further minor scalar sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, and expansion-factor tweaks because nine no-improve rounds means scalar tuning is exhausted. I also moved away from low-rank, whitening, and gating after repeated clear losses, while keeping K fixed at a frontier-relevant value for a clean architecture-only read.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 44 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a simpler non-lowrank residual architecture after `multi_branch_gated` and `jumprelu` both failed badly at K=24.","Keep the test architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields explicitly pinned.","`two_stage_residual` checks whether hierarchical residual coding helps mid-K without the added complexity of low-rank trunks or learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether staged residual coding helps more under tighter budgets.","If `two_stage_residual` clearly loses at K=24, reject this branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `batch_topk` or `residual_vq` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `two_stage_residual` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain is localized or extends across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Now that `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is integrated, an architecture-only run at `K=16, EF=12` can test whether router-guided support selection improves the mid-low-K frontier over the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` point (`FVU=0.10792168974876404`) without changing optimization or width.","summary":"Round 19 was rejected on isolation grounds before producing a training result, so the clean follow-up is to execute the already-integrated family as a pure architecture comparison. Run `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=16, EF=12` with the established low-K signum recipe and no code changes this round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This fixes the previous policy issue by removing code edits from the round and keeping the experiment to a single primary variable: architecture. The main risk is that the routed variant may need router-strength calibration, but the first priority is obtaining a valid comparable datapoint at the target frontier slot.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 was policy-rejected before execution because code-edit introduction and architecture change were coupled; treat the family as already integrated and schedule a pure architecture-only run next.","Use the exact low-K baseline recipe when evaluating `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` so the comparison against the current `K=16, EF=12` frontier point is clean."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` wins at `K=16`, run the same family at `K=24, EF=12` to test transfer along the adjacent frontier slot.","If it is close but worse than baseline, keep the family alive and test a smaller routing perturbation in a later code round.","If it clearly loses at `K=16`, return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` and resume smaller-K frontier work there."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0145.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` worsened the `K=16` bucketed run, so the next exploitation step should test whether the current low-K bucketed recipe is learning-rate mismatched rather than fundamentally saturated. A lower `LR=4e-4` is the highest-priority single-variable probe because it is explicitly suggested by the latest result and may improve convergence stability at the current practical lower-bound anchor.","summary":"Run a pure learning-rate sweep on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`, keeping architecture, optimizer, aux loss, preprocessing, and `EF=16` fixed while changing only `LR` from `3.2e-3` to `4e-4`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the exploitation policy after four non-improving rounds, avoids new architectures, and changes exactly one parameter. I chose the `K=16` anchor because it is the most valuable exposed small-K bucketed point after `K=8` failed, and improving it would matter more for the frontier than polishing already-strong high-K anchors.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 145 continues exploitation on the bucketed backbone after the stronger aux-loss probe underperformed, shifting to an LR-only test at the most valuable low-K anchor.","This round isolates whether the `K=16` bucketed recipe is overshooting under `LR=3.2e-3`; `LR=4e-4` is the first lower-LR probe because it is closer to the current working regime than `2e-4` while still being a substantial stability test."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` improves `K=16`, propagate that LR to `K=24` to test whether the gain generalizes across the low-K bucketed frontier.","If `LR=4e-4` underperforms but training is smooth, test the remaining lower LR `2e-4` before concluding that this backbone truly prefers the higher step size.","If `LR=4e-4` clearly slows convergence too much, restore `LR=3.2e-3` as the bucketed baseline and shift the next round to a preprocessing or optimizer probe rather than further low-LR descent."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
