research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0045.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After repeated failures from residual/gating variants, relaxing the per-sample hard support constraint may recover a better mid-K tradeoff: `batch_topk` at `K=24, EF=12` could improve reconstruction efficiency over fixed-sample top-k and challenge the current `K=24` frontier point without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `batch_topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by trying a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism instead of any further scalar sweep.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, K, and EF tweaks because ten no-improve rounds means minor tuning is exhausted. I also kept the comparison at K=24 so the readout stays directly comparable to the current frontier slot while testing a genuinely different support-allocation mechanism.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 45 continues severe-stagnation recovery with another fundamentally different built-in family after `multi_branch_gated`, `jumprelu`, and `two_stage_residual` all failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields explicitly pinned.","`batch_topk` tests whether a looser support-budget allocation works better than strict per-sample top-k in the frontier-relevant mid-K regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether flexible budget allocation helps more at tighter sparsity.","If `batch_topk` clearly loses at K=24, reject this support-allocation branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `residual_vq` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `batch_topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Plain gating clearly loses at `K=8`, but the low-K bottleneck may still be the hardness of support selection rather than the low-rank residual backbone itself. The next single-variable probe should test whether the smoother `JumpReLU` selector helps the low-rank residual family recover quality at the allowed low-K anchor `K=8`.","summary":"Run one parameter-only architecture comparison at `K=8` with `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. Success criterion: beat the current `K=8` frontier anchor FVU (`0.12280897796154022`) and show that smoothing support selection improves low-K reconstruction where hard top-k gating failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the allowed K set, avoids repeating the failed gating hypothesis, and tests a genuinely different existing mechanism at the most decision-relevant low-K anchor. It is a better next move than another rerun because the `lowrank_gated_residual` miss at `K=8` was clear rather than borderline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 should pivot from plain gating to a smoother support-selection mechanism at the same allowed low-K anchor after `lowrank_gated_residual` clearly lost at `K=8` (`0.12682607769966125`) versus the incumbent `K=8` frontier (`0.12280897796154022`).","New hypothesis: `JumpReLU` may help specifically in the tight-budget `K=8` regime by smoothing latent selection without requiring a new family integration step, while keeping the low-rank residual backbone and the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 recipe constant.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` also loses clearly at `K=8`, that is evidence that support-selection tweaks alone are unlikely to displace the soft-codebook anchor in the allowed low-K lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` wins at `K=8`, test the same family at `K=16` to see whether the gain extends beyond the lowest allowed anchor.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=8`, do one confirmatory rerun before retiring the idea.","If it clearly loses at `K=8`, shift away from selector-only changes and toward a more structural existing mechanism or a carefully differentiated new family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0112.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After thirteen non-improving rounds, the next useful step is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; `bucketed_lowrank_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff by routing samples between specialized low-rank residual dictionaries instead of forcing one global selector.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the recent K=24 probes across adaptive-budget, gated, and JumpReLU support-selection variants all failed to beat the current frontier. The next clean architecture comparison should stay on the valuable `K=24` anchor but switch to `bucketed_lowrank_residual`, which offers a distinct conditional-dictionary mechanism from the families tried in rounds 109 to 111 while keeping the rest of the strong EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe fixed. This isolates architecture alone and tests whether sample-conditioned dictionary choice is more effective than changing only the selector.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than making another minor tweak, keeps K within the allowed operator set, and targets a meaningful smaller-K frontier slot. The main risk is that prior older-budget evidence for this family was not strong, but it remains a more distinct and defensible next probe than revisiting recently failing selector variants.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` also lost at `K=24`, recent selector-focused low-rank branches remain uncompetitive against the current mid-K frontier.","Round 112 should test `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as a more structurally different conditional-dictionary mechanism.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture rather than recipe drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the conditional-dictionary benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to recent selector variants.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0108.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After nine non-improving rounds, the next useful move is a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than another low-rank/codebook variant; `adaptive_budget_topk` may improve the K=24 tradeoff by reallocating support across examples while keeping the same average sparsity target.","summary":"Severe stagnation is still active, so this round should not spend effort on more soft-codebook or scalar recipe tweaks. Run one architecture-comparison experiment at the valuable smaller-K anchor `K=24` with `adaptive_budget_topk`, holding the rest of the strong EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe fixed. This tests a qualitatively different dynamic-budget selector that has not been explored in the current search history and is directly aligned with the policy guidance to try a fundamentally different architecture.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"adaptive_budget_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than tuning within a losing family, and it keeps K within the allowed operator set. The main risk is that the simpler non-low-rank baseline may underperform on absolute FVU, but the mechanism is different enough to justify one clean probe at the K=24 frontier slot.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_budget_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_residual_vq` also lost at `K=24`, severe stagnation remained active and the search should continue with a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than more low-rank or codebook variations.","Round 108 should probe `adaptive_budget_topk` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe to test whether dynamic budget allocation helps the mid-K Pareto lane.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adaptive_budget_topk` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the dynamic-budget benefit persists in the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another fundamentally different non-codebook mechanism rather than returning to soft-codebook cleanup.","If it runs but is noisy and close, do one confirmatory repeat at the same `K=24` anchor before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0143.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` stayed on a smooth enough degradation path when moving from `K=24` to `K=16` (`FVU 0.0889 -> 0.1015`), so the highest-value single-variable probe is to continue the same descent to `K=8`. Even with a further FVU increase, a credible `K=8, EF=16` point could extend the Pareto frontier toward materially lower online cost.","summary":"Run a pure K-axis experiment on the current strongest EF=16 backbone by holding recipe and preprocessing fixed and reducing only `K` from 16 to 8.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This respects the one-variable rule and keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16` pinned. I am deferring the hinted optimizer/preprocessing probes by one round because round 142 produced a useful smaller-K archive point, so the cleanest next frontier-maintenance action is to finish mapping whether this backbone still has a viable `K=8` tradeoff.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 143 hypothesis: continue the pure K-axis descent on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` by testing `K=8` with architecture, optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing unchanged.","Rationale: round 142 showed a moderate rather than catastrophic degradation at `K=16`, so `K=8` is now the highest-information remaining point on the allowed K grid for determining how far this backbone can extend the low-K frontier under the fixed EF=16 regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` forms a non-dominated point, continue the same K-axis descent to `K=4` to map the extreme low-K tail on this backbone.","If `K=8` regresses sharply, keep `K=16` as the practical lower bound for this recipe and shift the next round to a preprocessing probe such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` at fixed `K=24` or `K=16`.","If `K=8` is close but noisy, run one confirmatory repeat before concluding whether the bucketed backbone truly supports the sub-16 regime."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0064.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` has now entered the frontier at K=16 and was already close at K=24, so the next informative test is whether the same soft coarse residual coding can also compete at K=32 and give the family multiple Pareto-frontier wins across the mid-K band.","summary":"Run a pure parameter comparison for `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32` while keeping the rest of the winning recipe fixed. The family already produced a near-frontier K=24 result and now owns K=16, so the highest-value next step is to map whether its gains persist at the larger covered mid-K anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This keeps a single hypothesis and changes only K, which cleanly tests whether the new family generalizes across the mid-K regime. The main risk is that `lowrank_two_stage_residual` remains stronger at K=32 even if the soft-codebook family helps at tighter sparsity, but the experiment is still high-value because a K=32 win would materially expand the family's frontier coverage.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 tests whether `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, now on the frontier at K=16 and near-frontier at K=24, can also compete at K=32.","Keep architecture and recipe fixed (`EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`) so K is the only changing variable.","Success criterion is beating the current K=32 anchor (`lowrank_two_stage_residual`, FVU 0.08931536227464676) or establishing another clearly competitive mid-K point for the family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` improves the K=32 anchor, test K=8 to see whether the family can cover an even broader low-K frontier band.","If it is close but slightly behind at K=32, consider one confirmatory rerun before deciding whether the family truly tops out around K=16-24.","If it clearly loses at K=32, keep the family as a K=16 specialist and resume searching for a different architecture for the larger mid-K slots."],"primary_variable":"k"}
