research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0124.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Under the fixed EF=16 regime, the simpler non-routed two-stage soft-codebook backbone may outperform the routed variant at K=16 because routing appears brittle to recipe changes while the base two-stage path has been the stronger mid-K workhorse.","summary":"Severe stagnation guidance says to stop minor tweaks and try a fundamentally different architecture. The last two recipe-only changes on the routed K=16 incumbent failed badly, so the next clean move is an architecture switch within the existing registered families. I am testing `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=16 with the stable signum recipe to see whether removing routing yields a better small-K tradeoff under the new fixed EF=16 policy.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement by changing architecture rather than applying another small recipe tweak. The main risk is that EF=16 regime drift still dominates the result, but this is a better diagnostic than continuing to perturb the clearly fragile routed K=16 setup.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 124 stops minor recipe tweaks after Hadamard and Adam both strongly degraded the routed K=16 incumbent.","Severe-stagnation policy now points to a fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more optimizer/preprocessing perturbations on the same family.","Test `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=16 as the simplest strong soft-codebook backbone to check whether routing is the source of fragility under EF=16."],"next_hypotheses":["If the non-routed two-stage soft-codebook model improves at K=16, follow with K=32 under the same EF=16 recipe to map whether the simpler backbone is broadly better in the fixed-EF regime.","If it still underperforms badly, test a more structurally different existing family such as `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=16 rather than returning to recipe tweaks.","If multiple existing architectures all regress under EF=16, prioritize diagnosing fixed-EF regime shift with a direct EF16 control narrative instead of attributing the failures to optimizer or preprocessing alone."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
